1
00:04:43,101 --> 00:04:45,301
'What's the impact of
all of this on the market?'

2
00:04:45,421 --> 00:04:48,861
'You will just have to take a minute to
assess how the market has digested this news'

3
00:04:48,941 --> 00:04:49,941
'of this crime...'

4
00:04:50,181 --> 00:04:52,261
Mom, you used to say
that making a will is ominous

5
00:04:53,061 --> 00:04:55,221
as it nears a person's death.

6
00:04:56,381 --> 00:04:59,701
But you died young even
though you didn't make a will.

7
00:05:00,141 --> 00:05:02,901
Now I can't even say,
'Where there is a will,'

8
00:05:04,821 --> 00:05:05,821
'there is a way.'

9
00:05:19,501 --> 00:05:22,341
Look, mom. I had invested in shares.

10
00:05:22,701 --> 00:05:23,381
Even that is incurring a loss.

11
00:05:23,461 --> 00:05:25,821
Saturn is not in a favourable position.

12
00:05:25,901 --> 00:05:28,581
And today, I have to
again go to the registrar.

13
00:05:30,221 --> 00:05:32,581
You didn't give a will. At least
give me blessings. Please.

14
00:05:32,821 --> 00:05:34,581
Offer Rs 500.

15
00:05:34,941 --> 00:05:37,941
The blessing of Gods and
Goddesses is also important.

16
00:05:47,821 --> 00:05:48,861
Mr Lal.

17
00:05:48,941 --> 00:05:49,581
Yes, sir.

18
00:05:49,941 --> 00:05:54,141
If I say something wrong,
you will file a case against me.

19
00:05:55,341 --> 00:05:56,341
No, sir.

20
00:05:56,541 --> 00:05:59,101
But what to do? I can't do anything.

21
00:05:59,301 --> 00:06:03,021
Look, Ranvir. The land
isn't in your mother's name.

22
00:06:03,221 --> 00:06:03,621
Sir...

23
00:06:03,741 --> 00:06:07,621
Kukreja builder claims
that your late grandpa

24
00:06:07,741 --> 00:06:08,941
had made a will.

25
00:06:09,101 --> 00:06:10,701
But he gave it to a trust.

26
00:06:11,501 --> 00:06:15,901
Later, the trust transferred the
entire property in Kukreja's name.

27
00:06:15,941 --> 00:06:16,221
No. No. That's impossible, sir.

28
00:06:16,341 --> 00:06:17,781
The matter got closed then.

29
00:06:18,341 --> 00:06:20,581
In my family there is no
system of making a will.

30
00:06:20,661 --> 00:06:20,901
Oh!

31
00:06:20,941 --> 00:06:21,941
But legally...

32
00:06:22,261 --> 00:06:22,661
Legally.

33
00:06:22,741 --> 00:06:25,421
The next generation family
has a claim on ancestral property.

34
00:06:25,501 --> 00:06:25,901
Yes.

35
00:06:25,941 --> 00:06:28,941
It means, after my grandpa's death
my mother inherited the property.

36
00:06:29,061 --> 00:06:31,141
And after her death, I am the rightful owner
of this property. Because the paperwork...

37
00:06:31,221 --> 00:06:32,301
And your uncle.

38
00:06:32,381 --> 00:06:32,701
What?

39
00:06:33,061 --> 00:06:33,941
Uncle?

40
00:06:34,101 --> 00:06:35,861
What uncle? What do
you have to do with uncle?

41
00:06:35,941 --> 00:06:38,941
According to document, if
someone can claim that land

42
00:06:39,101 --> 00:06:43,261
after your mother's
death, it's only your uncle.

43
00:06:45,821 --> 00:06:46,901
What's his name?

44
00:06:47,461 --> 00:06:51,061
Sir, invitation from the builder in Mahim.

45
00:06:59,181 --> 00:07:00,261
Madho Singh Rathore.

46
00:07:00,821 --> 00:07:05,581
But he went away. Went far away.

47
00:07:05,661 --> 00:07:07,941
We tried to find him. We even
gave ads in the newspaper.

48
00:07:08,101 --> 00:07:08,781
But...

49
00:07:08,901 --> 00:07:10,021
But we didn't get any response, sir.

50
00:07:10,141 --> 00:07:12,181
Yes. It means, the property
should be transferred in my name.

51
00:07:12,261 --> 00:07:15,541
Sir, look. She is my mother.
The land belongs to my mother.

52
00:07:15,621 --> 00:07:17,781
What belongs to my mother why
do you want to give it to my uncle?

53
00:07:17,901 --> 00:07:21,301
And Kukreja's claim is totally baseless.

54
00:07:21,381 --> 00:07:22,381
This is crime.

55
00:07:22,581 --> 00:07:23,301
Fraud and forgery.

56
00:07:23,421 --> 00:07:23,701
Total.

57
00:07:23,821 --> 00:07:27,861
Look. If you want to file a criminal
case, why did you come here?

58
00:07:29,261 --> 00:07:31,941
I look after civil property matters.

59
00:07:32,061 --> 00:07:32,501
Yes, sir.

60
00:07:32,581 --> 00:07:35,661
And you know. You are
his lawyer. Explain it to him.

61
00:07:35,741 --> 00:07:39,861
Sir, you see, we are looking for his uncle.

62
00:07:39,941 --> 00:07:42,221
But we got this notice from your office.

63
00:07:42,341 --> 00:07:44,141
So we thought we should meet you.

64
00:07:44,661 --> 00:07:46,341
Now you have only one chance.

65
00:07:47,381 --> 00:07:48,901
Within a month bring your uncle

66
00:07:49,141 --> 00:07:53,381
and his no objection certificate here.

67
00:07:54,141 --> 00:07:55,261
Then we will think about it.

68
00:07:56,781 --> 00:07:57,781
Yes.

69
00:07:59,061 --> 00:08:00,181
Goodbye.

70
00:08:01,381 --> 00:08:02,381
Thanks...

71
00:08:14,301 --> 00:08:15,181
Hello.

72
00:08:15,301 --> 00:08:17,301
Yes. He just left my office.

73
00:08:17,421 --> 00:08:18,821
He had brought that buffoon along with him.

74
00:08:18,941 --> 00:08:19,381
Yes.

75
00:08:19,501 --> 00:08:20,381
I gave him one month's time.

76
00:08:20,501 --> 00:08:22,661
Don't worry about
that. I'll take care of it.

77
00:08:22,741 --> 00:08:25,661
I am after him. I am
following him like a shadow.

78
00:08:25,741 --> 00:08:25,941
Yes.

79
00:08:26,701 --> 00:08:28,941
I'm just waiting for
one mistake on his part.

80
00:08:29,101 --> 00:08:31,261
I'll set the wheels in motion
as soon as that happens.

81
00:08:33,501 --> 00:08:36,821
Now, how will you escape
from Kukreja's clutches?

82
00:08:38,621 --> 00:08:41,461
I am Kukreja. Right now, I'm a
contractor. Soon I'll become a builder.

83
00:08:42,821 --> 00:08:46,701
Nobody can stop me
from constructing Sun City!

84
00:08:47,261 --> 00:08:50,501
Whose call is it?

85
00:08:51,501 --> 00:08:53,501
Oh God, Salim.

86
00:08:53,621 --> 00:08:54,501
Kukreja.

87
00:08:54,621 --> 00:08:56,701
Salim, hello.

88
00:08:56,781 --> 00:08:58,221
Can you hear me?

89
00:08:58,301 --> 00:09:00,181
Yes, Salim. Tell me.

90
00:09:00,301 --> 00:09:01,661
What happened about Shakuntala Niwas?

91
00:09:01,741 --> 00:09:05,141
I've given you my word. I'll have
it vacated by the deadline. Period.

92
00:09:05,261 --> 00:09:06,541
Listen, you moron.

93
00:09:06,901 --> 00:09:09,941
If it doesn't happen this time, I
will kill you before the deadline.

94
00:09:14,421 --> 00:09:15,421
Mr Lal, listen to me.

95
00:09:16,341 --> 00:09:18,741
Tomorrow I will go to the
registrar's office for the last time.

96
00:09:18,861 --> 00:09:21,141
If fair means don't work,
I will use foul means.

97
00:09:21,261 --> 00:09:23,381
You just trace uncle anyhow.

98
00:09:24,421 --> 00:09:25,941
Why do you worry?

99
00:09:26,221 --> 00:09:29,941
Everything can be done in half rate. You just
have to grease their palms. I will get it done.

100
00:09:30,181 --> 00:09:32,461
Yes. I will hang up now.

101
00:09:39,701 --> 00:09:44,861
I told you. Nothing can
be done without uncle.

102
00:09:44,941 --> 00:09:47,821
Sir, I will bring him
provided I know where he is.

103
00:09:47,901 --> 00:09:50,381
Sir, I just want you to delay
the hearing as much as possible.

104
00:09:50,941 --> 00:09:52,541
If you want, you can do anything.

105
00:09:53,221 --> 00:09:53,781
Yes. Right.

106
00:09:53,861 --> 00:09:54,941
You know what to...

107
00:09:55,381 --> 00:09:58,861
That's better. I was also
waiting. For the money.

108
00:09:58,941 --> 00:10:01,101
Please help me.

109
00:10:03,341 --> 00:10:05,621
What is this? So less?

110
00:10:05,701 --> 00:10:07,461
Pennies for property worth billions.

111
00:10:07,541 --> 00:10:08,381
Look, this is the true state of our courts.

112
00:10:08,461 --> 00:10:10,341
This is what happens at our courts.

113
00:10:10,421 --> 00:10:15,621
The person who is giving the bribe... His name is Ranvir Singh.
- Ranvir Singh.

114
00:10:15,901 --> 00:10:18,781
'Yes. Let me tell you.
His name is Ranvir Singh.'

115
00:10:23,101 --> 00:10:26,621
'See for yourself how
an innocent looking man'

116
00:10:26,741 --> 00:10:29,341
'is impugning the nation with
his illegal deeds and black money.'

117
00:10:29,461 --> 00:10:31,861
'Okay, ma'am. Tell me. For
how long have you known Ranvir?'

118
00:10:32,101 --> 00:10:37,301
'I know him since the time he
broke the glasses of my house.'

119
00:10:37,421 --> 00:10:38,941
'He is a notorious child.'

120
00:10:39,021 --> 00:10:40,341
'Notorious! Did you hear that?'

121
00:10:40,461 --> 00:10:41,581
I live in Mumbai, sir.

122
00:10:41,661 --> 00:10:42,901
You just heard what he
neighbour had to say about him.

123
00:10:42,941 --> 00:10:44,581
I don't say much.

124
00:10:45,221 --> 00:10:48,701
I am saying that I was not giving him bribe.
I was giving him money to fetch cigarette.

125
00:10:49,341 --> 00:10:52,061
The entire nation saw you
asking him to get you a cigarette.

126
00:10:52,181 --> 00:10:52,701
Did you understand?

127
00:10:52,781 --> 00:10:55,661
'Let's hope that the court gives
him the severest punishment.'

128
00:10:56,941 --> 00:10:58,141
Whose call is it?

129
00:10:59,221 --> 00:11:01,421
Sir, it's my share broker's
call. I will make a call, sir.

130
00:11:01,501 --> 00:11:04,421
Did you hear that? Mr
Smarty-pants wishes to take the call.

131
00:11:04,941 --> 00:11:06,381
What work do you do?

132
00:11:06,621 --> 00:11:07,621
Event management, sir.

133
00:11:08,421 --> 00:11:10,741
You mean, catering.

134
00:11:11,901 --> 00:11:12,901
Not catering, sir.

135
00:11:13,421 --> 00:11:15,501
Arranging for food and lodging for people.

136
00:11:15,701 --> 00:11:17,101
Handling big actors' needs.

137
00:11:17,221 --> 00:11:18,381
Sir, let me make just one call.

138
00:11:18,501 --> 00:11:19,701
Why did you go to that office?

139
00:11:19,941 --> 00:11:22,141
Sir, I had gone to transfer
my own property in my name.

140
00:11:22,621 --> 00:11:23,341
Property?

141
00:11:23,501 --> 00:11:24,501
Yes.

142
00:11:25,501 --> 00:11:26,421
Property.

143
00:11:26,541 --> 00:11:27,061
Yes.

144
00:11:27,421 --> 00:11:28,461
Where is your property?

145
00:11:28,581 --> 00:11:29,861
Sir, Bandra.

146
00:11:33,901 --> 00:11:34,901
Bandra?

147
00:11:36,261 --> 00:11:37,261
Yes.

148
00:11:38,501 --> 00:11:39,061
Shinde.

149
00:11:39,181 --> 00:11:39,581
Yes, sir.

150
00:11:39,701 --> 00:11:40,701
Did you see that?

151
00:11:41,261 --> 00:11:42,421
He owns a property in Bandra.

152
00:11:43,261 --> 00:11:44,821
And he had only Rs 800 in his pocket.

153
00:11:45,621 --> 00:11:49,301
He gave a self-cheque.
Get cash for it. And listen.

154
00:11:49,381 --> 00:11:49,821
Yes.

155
00:11:49,941 --> 00:11:53,541
In the report write that the
guy gave money for cigarette.

156
00:11:53,621 --> 00:11:54,221
Okay?

157
00:11:54,341 --> 00:11:54,581
Yes, sir.

158
00:11:54,701 --> 00:11:56,141
And get me a cigarette on your way back.

159
00:11:56,221 --> 00:11:57,501
What are you saying, Mr Parekh?

160
00:11:57,621 --> 00:11:58,701
It's gone, Mr Ranvir.

161
00:11:58,781 --> 00:11:59,141
How much?

162
00:11:59,261 --> 00:12:00,941
I'll be left stranded on the streets!

163
00:12:01,101 --> 00:12:03,381
The market has crashed
further due to the rallies.

164
00:12:03,501 --> 00:12:03,901
Crashed? What do you mean?

165
00:12:03,941 --> 00:12:06,341
Excuse me. Give me Rs 100.

166
00:12:06,461 --> 00:12:07,941
Darn! What rotten luck!

167
00:12:08,101 --> 00:12:09,781
Excuse me, sir.

168
00:12:11,061 --> 00:12:11,781
What is it?

169
00:12:11,861 --> 00:12:12,781
Give me Rs 50.

170
00:12:12,861 --> 00:12:13,941
Didn't you hear me talking?

171
00:12:14,221 --> 00:12:15,581
Shall I connect you to the stock exchange?

172
00:12:15,661 --> 00:12:16,461
Give me Rs 25.

173
00:12:16,541 --> 00:12:18,581
My shares are gone.

174
00:12:19,941 --> 00:12:21,501
I am sorry. It's not your fault.

175
00:12:21,581 --> 00:12:24,941
But if this goes on, I will have
to become your business partner.

176
00:12:25,621 --> 00:12:26,621
Mine?

177
00:12:30,621 --> 00:12:31,621
He has left.

178
00:12:33,661 --> 00:12:36,381
Give Ranvir an offer of Rs 10 million.

179
00:12:38,181 --> 00:12:39,261
Give him a cheque.

180
00:12:39,941 --> 00:12:40,941
And make him sign the documents.

181
00:12:41,101 --> 00:12:41,341
Okay.

182
00:12:41,421 --> 00:12:42,941
Later, I will do stop payment.

183
00:12:43,861 --> 00:12:44,581
But, sir.

184
00:12:44,701 --> 00:12:44,941
Yes.

185
00:12:45,061 --> 00:12:46,301
That plot is worth Rs 200 million. Right?

186
00:12:46,381 --> 00:12:46,901
Yes.

187
00:12:46,941 --> 00:12:50,261
If you're going to stop the payment later
on, give him a cheque of Rs 200 million.

188
00:13:02,781 --> 00:13:03,941
Moron!

189
00:13:04,461 --> 00:13:07,341
How many times will you remind me
that there is no money in the account?

190
00:13:07,821 --> 00:13:09,541
You fool.

191
00:13:10,181 --> 00:13:11,141
Do as much as you are told. Understood?

192
00:13:11,261 --> 00:13:11,741
Yes.

193
00:13:11,901 --> 00:13:12,261
Yes.

194
00:13:12,381 --> 00:13:13,381
Get going!

195
00:13:16,461 --> 00:13:18,301
But how could you do this?

196
00:13:19,061 --> 00:13:21,421
And that too in front of the
press. In front of the media.

197
00:13:21,501 --> 00:13:23,461
Sir, I didn't know that
the press would be there.

198
00:13:23,661 --> 00:13:24,741
If you just...

199
00:13:25,101 --> 00:13:26,101
Listen.

200
00:13:26,621 --> 00:13:31,181
I can't tolerate bad publicity of
my dream project at any cost.

201
00:13:33,741 --> 00:13:38,021
It is better that you yourself
leave the project immediately.

202
00:13:38,821 --> 00:13:39,821
For good.

203
00:14:07,581 --> 00:14:08,781
Move!

204
00:14:08,901 --> 00:14:09,261
Hello.

205
00:14:09,381 --> 00:14:10,701
Hello, Mr Ranvir. Hello.

206
00:14:10,781 --> 00:14:11,141
Be careful.

207
00:14:11,221 --> 00:14:13,061
Yes, Mr Lal. What's the bad news?

208
00:14:13,461 --> 00:14:16,941
It's not bad news. I have
good news. Good news.

209
00:14:17,181 --> 00:14:19,341
Your uncle has been found.

210
00:14:21,261 --> 00:14:22,821
Yes! Where did you find him?

211
00:14:22,901 --> 00:14:25,141
He is not in London. He is here, in India.

212
00:14:25,941 --> 00:14:27,421
I am speaking the truth.

213
00:14:28,301 --> 00:14:33,381
No! How did he find his uncle?
This is not going in our favour!

214
00:14:34,901 --> 00:14:36,741
Hello. Yes, Mr Lal.

215
00:14:37,341 --> 00:14:39,261
Mr Lal, I am in the lift. I can't hear you.

216
00:14:39,661 --> 00:14:40,661
Mr Lal. Hello.

217
00:14:41,421 --> 00:14:42,701
'Uncle, I am coming to get you.'

218
00:14:57,381 --> 00:14:59,181
We've reached Jaipur. In an hour.

219
00:15:00,941 --> 00:15:01,941
Jaipur has its own beauty.

220
00:15:03,061 --> 00:15:03,701
How much did it cost?

221
00:15:04,141 --> 00:15:05,061
Sir, Rs 880.

222
00:15:05,141 --> 00:15:06,861
What? How? How come Rs 880?

223
00:15:07,021 --> 00:15:09,821
Sir, he said to bring 1 cup tea
and 2 'samosas'. What can I do?

224
00:15:09,901 --> 00:15:11,021
Hey!

225
00:15:11,341 --> 00:15:12,941
You were craving to have tea in the air.

226
00:15:13,021 --> 00:15:14,501
Couldn't you have waited for an hour?

227
00:15:17,341 --> 00:15:18,821
Look, handle your goat.

228
00:15:19,341 --> 00:15:20,701
Sir, carefully.

229
00:15:20,781 --> 00:15:22,221
Darn!

230
00:15:29,821 --> 00:15:32,661
This time Congress
will surely win. I swear.

231
00:15:33,101 --> 00:15:34,261
So let's bet for Rs 125.

232
00:15:34,741 --> 00:15:36,141
I will shave off my moustache.

233
00:15:36,461 --> 00:15:38,301
This time the opposition will win.

234
00:15:38,381 --> 00:15:39,061
Fine.

235
00:15:39,141 --> 00:15:41,621
It is so cramped in here. Three
people are sitting on two seats.

236
00:15:41,741 --> 00:15:43,221
What have I got myself into!

237
00:15:47,821 --> 00:15:49,221
He is bothering me.

238
00:15:52,341 --> 00:15:53,141
Hello.

239
00:15:53,261 --> 00:15:54,261
Hello, Ranvir.

240
00:15:54,581 --> 00:15:54,941
Yes, Mr Lal.

241
00:15:55,061 --> 00:15:56,061
Did you reach Rajasthan?

242
00:15:56,821 --> 00:15:58,221
Okay. I am coming in two days with uncle.

243
00:15:58,341 --> 00:16:00,021
Hold on. Listen to me.

244
00:16:00,341 --> 00:16:02,741
Kukreja has given an
offer of Rs 10 million.

245
00:16:02,941 --> 00:16:03,461
What do I do now? Shall I accept it?

246
00:16:03,541 --> 00:16:04,541
I just don't understand.

247
00:16:04,821 --> 00:16:05,541
Rs 10 million?

248
00:16:05,621 --> 00:16:06,621
Yes.

249
00:16:07,621 --> 00:16:08,301
No way!

250
00:16:08,421 --> 00:16:10,661
Hello. The signal is breaking. Hello.

251
00:16:10,941 --> 00:16:12,781
Hello. I can't hear you.

252
00:16:12,901 --> 00:16:13,941
Hold him.

253
00:16:15,861 --> 00:16:18,421
Looks like he had eaten
sprouts this morning!

254
00:16:27,141 --> 00:16:30,581
Stop the bus. Stop the
bus. I want to get down.

255
00:16:31,541 --> 00:16:32,301
Stop the bus.

256
00:16:32,381 --> 00:16:34,261
He got scared.

257
00:16:35,941 --> 00:16:36,941
Idiots!

258
00:16:55,221 --> 00:16:56,221
He sat down, sir.

259
00:16:56,461 --> 00:16:57,181
Look there.

260
00:16:57,421 --> 00:17:01,101
So many mutton dishes.

261
00:17:12,141 --> 00:17:16,941
Hey! Stop! Stop the rickshaw!

262
00:17:23,541 --> 00:17:25,301
Stop!

263
00:17:25,941 --> 00:17:26,941
Excuse me...

264
00:17:27,061 --> 00:17:29,461
Are you crazy? Why are
you showing me your thumb?

265
00:17:30,221 --> 00:17:32,101
Sorry. I was asking if I could get a ride.

266
00:17:32,181 --> 00:17:33,461
Then why don't you just say it?

267
00:17:33,581 --> 00:17:36,181
No vehicle will stop if
you show your thumb.

268
00:17:36,301 --> 00:17:37,341
Please stop.

269
00:17:37,461 --> 00:17:38,901
Come on! Come quickly.

270
00:17:39,941 --> 00:17:41,661
Come on!

271
00:17:44,261 --> 00:17:45,461
Come on, let's get going.

272
00:18:30,501 --> 00:18:33,181
Darn!

273
00:18:42,461 --> 00:18:43,461
Hello.

274
00:18:44,941 --> 00:18:46,461
Why did they make a door here?

275
00:18:46,941 --> 00:18:48,301
They should have made a wall here.

276
00:18:57,301 --> 00:18:59,581
Hello.

277
00:19:11,061 --> 00:19:12,061
Excuse me.

278
00:19:13,301 --> 00:19:14,341
Hello.

279
00:19:14,821 --> 00:19:17,021
I am your nephew. Ranvir.

280
00:19:26,301 --> 00:19:28,261
Madho Singh Rathore.

281
00:19:32,141 --> 00:19:33,701
Shakuntala is your sister.

282
00:19:34,581 --> 00:19:36,581
I am Ranvir Singh. Her son.

283
00:19:58,061 --> 00:19:59,941
He has a striking face, sir.

284
00:20:02,141 --> 00:20:03,141
Show me.

285
00:20:05,581 --> 00:20:07,621
His features are also okay.

286
00:20:09,621 --> 00:20:12,061
But his physique and height
are not like that of Thakurs.

287
00:20:30,501 --> 00:20:33,341
If you are really my nephew Dholu.

288
00:20:33,781 --> 00:20:34,781
Ranvir.

289
00:20:37,501 --> 00:20:38,661
Remove your pants.

290
00:20:40,221 --> 00:20:41,781
Remove them.

291
00:20:41,901 --> 00:20:43,741
Your dignity won't wane
by removing the pants.

292
00:20:44,221 --> 00:20:46,941
Look, if you are my nephew

293
00:20:47,821 --> 00:20:50,301
then there should be a
mole on your derriere.

294
00:20:51,421 --> 00:20:52,661
I am sorry. What?

295
00:20:52,941 --> 00:20:55,741
In Rajasthani language
it means your buttocks.

296
00:20:56,101 --> 00:20:56,741
Buttocks?

297
00:20:56,821 --> 00:20:59,941
Yes. Buttocks. Your behind.

298
00:21:02,621 --> 00:21:03,621
Remove them.

299
00:21:08,821 --> 00:21:10,941
'There is no coyness in behaviour.'

300
00:21:12,501 --> 00:21:14,301
'People have become shameless.'

301
00:21:15,381 --> 00:21:20,261
'Despite being clothed, everyone's naked.'.

302
00:21:21,061 --> 00:21:22,061
What?

303
00:21:23,101 --> 00:21:25,021
Are you waiting for the right time?

304
00:21:26,021 --> 00:21:26,421
Show me.

305
00:21:26,861 --> 00:21:27,861
That spot.

306
00:21:28,941 --> 00:21:29,541
Show me.

307
00:21:29,901 --> 00:21:30,901
That spot.

308
00:21:41,861 --> 00:21:44,581
Dholu!

309
00:22:15,301 --> 00:22:18,541
What are you looking at? It's Saturday.

310
00:22:19,421 --> 00:22:21,181
He observes an oath
of silence on Saturdays.

311
00:22:38,261 --> 00:22:40,061
Painting from Oxford...

312
00:22:43,821 --> 00:22:44,341
Hello.

313
00:22:44,421 --> 00:22:45,901
Hello. Where are you?

314
00:22:46,461 --> 00:22:47,181
Did you find your uncle?

315
00:22:47,581 --> 00:22:48,581
Yes. I found him, Mr Lal. I found him.

316
00:22:48,701 --> 00:22:50,101
Great. Come back soon.

317
00:22:50,421 --> 00:22:53,781
By the way, I got a cheque of
Rs 10 million from Kukreja's office.

318
00:22:54,301 --> 00:22:58,261
Tell Kukreja to take the
cheque and keep it for retirement.

319
00:22:58,381 --> 00:23:00,421
When I will win the case,
he will become a pauper.

320
00:23:01,181 --> 00:23:02,941
An offer of Rs 10 million. What a...

321
00:23:03,941 --> 00:23:05,341
Okay. Tell me something.

322
00:23:05,861 --> 00:23:07,701
Our court's hearing is
not on Saturday, is it?

323
00:23:08,261 --> 00:23:12,261
Because uncle observes an
oath of silence on Saturdays.

324
00:23:12,381 --> 00:23:13,501
What? He observes an oath of silence?

325
00:23:13,621 --> 00:23:14,621
Yes.

326
00:23:15,781 --> 00:23:20,101
Are you sure your uncle will sign the will?

327
00:23:20,581 --> 00:23:23,141
I mean, what kind of man is your uncle?

328
00:23:23,861 --> 00:23:25,621
He is quite different.

329
00:23:26,701 --> 00:23:28,821
But he is highly educated and qualified.

330
00:23:28,901 --> 00:23:31,381
Listen, it's a very important matter.

331
00:23:32,061 --> 00:23:35,021
This time we won't get an extension.

332
00:23:35,501 --> 00:23:38,301
For sure. And another important matter.

333
00:23:38,741 --> 00:23:41,701
You have to pay my fees
of the past four months.

334
00:23:41,781 --> 00:23:42,341
Do something.

335
00:23:42,461 --> 00:23:43,261
Hello. Hello.

336
00:23:43,381 --> 00:23:44,061
Yes. Hello.

337
00:23:44,181 --> 00:23:45,141
Hello, Mr Lal. Hello. I can't hear you.

338
00:23:45,221 --> 00:23:45,661
Don't try to fool me, Ranvir.

339
00:23:46,221 --> 00:23:46,941
Hello...

340
00:23:47,061 --> 00:23:47,701
Hello. I can't understand
what you are saying.

341
00:23:47,821 --> 00:23:48,861
Mr Ranvir, don't do this. Please.

342
00:23:48,941 --> 00:23:49,741
Just listen to me...

343
00:23:49,861 --> 00:23:51,541
I can't hear you. Hello.

344
00:23:53,061 --> 00:23:55,341
Because of you I will
be sitting here all my life.

345
00:24:02,581 --> 00:24:05,381
Hello, Bhairav. Where is uncle?

346
00:24:05,741 --> 00:24:06,781
Did you see him?

347
00:24:08,221 --> 00:24:11,581
He has gone to the nearby
temple. For the 'puja'.

348
00:24:12,701 --> 00:24:13,701
Is it a special occasion?

349
00:24:14,941 --> 00:24:18,541
You did all the necessary rituals
on your mother's death anniversary.

350
00:24:19,341 --> 00:24:22,021
But he found out about
his sister's death last night.

351
00:24:23,021 --> 00:24:24,021
That too from you.

352
00:24:26,461 --> 00:24:27,461
Tell me something.

353
00:24:28,741 --> 00:24:30,541
How did you remember
him after so many years?

354
00:24:31,301 --> 00:24:33,261
Have you come to enquire
about his well-being?

355
00:24:34,461 --> 00:24:35,701
Or have you come for some work?

356
00:24:37,221 --> 00:24:38,581
After my parents' death,

357
00:24:40,861 --> 00:24:41,861
I had become alone.

358
00:24:44,021 --> 00:24:48,541
Then I thought instead of
living alone for my whole life.

359
00:24:49,461 --> 00:24:50,701
I should reconnect to my roots.

360
00:24:51,261 --> 00:24:52,741
That's why I came here to meet uncle.

361
00:24:53,421 --> 00:24:54,901
I want to take him to Mumbai with me.

362
00:24:56,341 --> 00:24:57,341
To my house.

363
00:24:58,701 --> 00:24:59,741
I had to inform him too.

364
00:25:04,861 --> 00:25:07,541
Tell me something. What took you so long?

365
00:25:10,101 --> 00:25:14,941
If you had to inform him, why
didn't you find him a year ago?

366
00:25:18,461 --> 00:25:22,701
As far as taking him along with
you to Mumbai is concerned...

367
00:25:22,821 --> 00:25:23,821
Yes.

368
00:25:24,061 --> 00:25:26,101
You should forget about it. He won't go.

369
00:25:28,621 --> 00:25:31,741
I think he is here. Hold on.

370
00:25:34,341 --> 00:25:35,341
Sir!

371
00:26:00,941 --> 00:26:01,941
Sir, bill.

372
00:26:07,541 --> 00:26:09,621
Are you smoking?
No.

373
00:26:09,781 --> 00:26:10,301
Are you tourists?

374
00:26:10,381 --> 00:26:10,581
No.

375
00:26:10,661 --> 00:26:11,661
No, sir.

376
00:26:11,901 --> 00:26:12,821
Why were you celebrating with drinks?

377
00:26:12,941 --> 00:26:13,821
We made a mistake.

378
00:26:13,941 --> 00:26:17,381
Here, I am in trouble. And
you guys are having fun.

379
00:26:27,301 --> 00:26:29,261
Today, after breaking your oath of silence

380
00:26:29,661 --> 00:26:31,421
which is the first word
that you will speak?

381
00:26:36,661 --> 00:26:37,701
Dholu.

382
00:26:38,621 --> 00:26:39,621
Come here.

383
00:26:46,381 --> 00:26:47,381
Take the holy offerings.

384
00:26:47,461 --> 00:26:48,461
Thank you, uncle.

385
00:26:55,101 --> 00:26:57,301
Uncle, I will surely finish this
board before I go to Mumbai.

386
00:26:57,381 --> 00:26:58,381
Tea is here.

387
00:27:01,221 --> 00:27:02,301
Tea.

388
00:27:03,661 --> 00:27:04,781
Special tea.

389
00:27:05,421 --> 00:27:06,341
Special tea.

390
00:27:06,421 --> 00:27:07,661
Hi, 'tea'! Thank you.

391
00:27:07,781 --> 00:27:08,221
Uncle Bhairav.

392
00:27:08,301 --> 00:27:09,381
Which one is mine?

393
00:27:09,501 --> 00:27:10,741
It's all the same. Take anyone.

394
00:27:11,861 --> 00:27:13,661
Listen, Bhairav. Where are you going?

395
00:27:16,421 --> 00:27:17,421
Tea.

396
00:27:17,861 --> 00:27:18,861
Thank you.

397
00:27:19,901 --> 00:27:22,821
She is Gulabo. We call her Gul.

398
00:27:23,701 --> 00:27:26,261
Hello, Gul. Sorry. I mean, Gulabo.

399
00:27:26,701 --> 00:27:27,701
I mean your name.

400
00:27:28,621 --> 00:27:29,621
She is my daughter.

401
00:27:29,901 --> 00:27:32,101
He means that he considers
her like his daughter.

402
00:27:32,221 --> 00:27:32,621
Biscuit.

403
00:27:33,141 --> 00:27:34,221
No, thank you.

404
00:27:34,781 --> 00:27:38,101
You see, the entire village
considers him as a father figure.

405
00:27:38,941 --> 00:27:41,501
She loves music and dance.

406
00:27:41,581 --> 00:27:42,581
Amazing.

407
00:27:44,581 --> 00:27:45,941
Music and dance.

408
00:27:54,261 --> 00:27:55,261
Yes. Tell me, Ranvir.

409
00:27:55,461 --> 00:27:58,181
Mr Lal, listen. I will send your
cheque as soon as I come there.

410
00:27:58,261 --> 00:27:58,661
Great.

411
00:27:58,781 --> 00:28:00,101
Why are you dying for money?

412
00:28:00,821 --> 00:28:02,181
You keep that cheque
of Rs 10 million. Fine?

413
00:28:02,261 --> 00:28:02,741
Okay, listen.

414
00:28:02,821 --> 00:28:03,301
Okay, listen.

415
00:28:03,421 --> 00:28:04,421
Yes, tell me.

416
00:28:04,781 --> 00:28:05,541
I had an idea.

417
00:28:05,661 --> 00:28:06,461
You got an idea.

418
00:28:06,581 --> 00:28:08,661
If uncle is unwell, can't you bring

419
00:28:10,221 --> 00:28:12,301
the registrar here for the signature?

420
00:28:12,621 --> 00:28:13,661
Impossible!

421
00:28:13,941 --> 00:28:16,701
Please leave the task
of thinking of ideas to me.

422
00:28:16,941 --> 00:28:19,461
And you just focus on
bringing your uncle here.

423
00:28:22,261 --> 00:28:22,661
Hello.

424
00:28:22,741 --> 00:28:23,221
Yes, sir.

425
00:28:23,301 --> 00:28:25,901
Listen, this time there
should be no mistake.

426
00:28:26,061 --> 00:28:26,501
Yes, sir.

427
00:28:27,061 --> 00:28:28,781
As my count ends, push him. Okay?

428
00:28:28,941 --> 00:28:29,941
Okay.

429
00:28:32,141 --> 00:28:34,941
Come on. Ten, nine...

430
00:28:36,061 --> 00:28:37,061
Eight...

431
00:28:37,821 --> 00:28:40,181
I am not telling you. You got angry.

432
00:28:40,581 --> 00:28:42,101
Two, one...

433
00:28:42,261 --> 00:28:42,781
One.

434
00:28:42,861 --> 00:28:43,341
Zero.

435
00:28:43,581 --> 00:28:43,941
Zero.

436
00:28:44,421 --> 00:28:47,021
Push him. Yes. Push him.

437
00:28:56,821 --> 00:28:58,621
Hello. Is the job done?

438
00:29:00,781 --> 00:29:01,861
We have fallen in the well.

439
00:29:03,221 --> 00:29:04,581
What are you doing?

440
00:29:04,941 --> 00:29:06,301
We are bathing.

441
00:29:06,861 --> 00:29:07,861
In the well?

442
00:29:08,341 --> 00:29:11,341
There was no water in our well.

443
00:29:12,301 --> 00:29:13,061
I don't know how to swim.

444
00:29:13,141 --> 00:29:14,821
This is a strange village.

445
00:29:18,421 --> 00:29:21,901
What are you doing there? I asked
you to push him. And you guys jumped in.

446
00:29:23,781 --> 00:29:24,861
Look at this. It's over.

447
00:29:29,301 --> 00:29:31,141
I told them to push him.

448
00:29:31,261 --> 00:29:33,701
Sir. Sir, call for you. It's Salim!

449
00:29:33,781 --> 00:29:38,541
Kukreja. Kukreja are
you listening? Hello. Hello.

450
00:29:50,941 --> 00:29:56,821
What? Covertly, secretly. Come here.

451
00:29:57,421 --> 00:30:02,181
Let's have a bet. If you
use this song in any film

452
00:30:02,701 --> 00:30:05,661
the film will be a hit for sure. I swear.

453
00:30:06,421 --> 00:30:09,661
Wow! Who knew that I'd also
get to meet a talented poet?

454
00:30:09,781 --> 00:30:10,781
Which poet?

455
00:30:11,141 --> 00:30:14,101
Never mind. The point
is that you sing really well.

456
00:30:14,181 --> 00:30:14,621
Me?

457
00:30:14,741 --> 00:30:15,741
Yes.

458
00:30:19,461 --> 00:30:20,101
Rainfall.

459
00:30:20,541 --> 00:30:23,341
Rainfall. Shall I sing a rain song?

460
00:30:23,621 --> 00:30:24,661
No. Don't.

461
00:30:24,741 --> 00:30:26,181
No. A rain song.

462
00:30:26,301 --> 00:30:27,461
No?

463
00:30:27,541 --> 00:30:28,541
No.

464
00:30:28,781 --> 00:30:31,461
Bhairav, tell me something.
Don't you ever go to the city?

465
00:30:32,501 --> 00:30:34,301
Don't you get bored in the village?

466
00:30:35,701 --> 00:30:36,741
What do I tell you?

467
00:30:37,581 --> 00:30:43,101
It's been ages since your uncle
has stepped out of this village.

468
00:30:43,661 --> 00:30:45,901
How will he go to the city?

469
00:30:46,861 --> 00:30:47,861
Okay, Bhairav.

470
00:30:48,141 --> 00:30:49,581
What other interesting
things are there in the village?

471
00:30:49,701 --> 00:30:52,461
There are many more things.
Okay. I will sing and tell you.

472
00:30:52,581 --> 00:30:53,061
Sing?

473
00:30:53,301 --> 00:30:54,461
One.

474
00:30:56,701 --> 00:30:58,581
Uncle, there is nothing here.

475
00:30:59,461 --> 00:31:00,461
This...

476
00:31:00,901 --> 00:31:05,701
Yes. Eating out means eating out.

477
00:31:06,301 --> 00:31:09,421
This is what your mother Shakuntala liked.

478
00:31:09,941 --> 00:31:14,341
Every Saturday after going to the
temple we would come here and eat.

479
00:31:14,461 --> 00:31:20,061
Yes. And look, today, he has come to this
place near the hill after 1 year and 3 months.

480
00:31:20,821 --> 00:31:22,261
And that too because of Dholu.

481
00:31:22,741 --> 00:31:24,421
This evening is for Dholu.

482
00:31:25,341 --> 00:31:30,341
Dholu, today when you will eat food
cooked by sir you will lick your fingers.

483
00:31:48,421 --> 00:31:51,261
Filmy songs in this lovely place, Dholu.

484
00:31:51,381 --> 00:31:51,781
Yes.

485
00:31:51,861 --> 00:31:54,781
Uncle filmy songs are also songs.

486
00:31:54,861 --> 00:31:55,621
No. No.

487
00:31:55,901 --> 00:31:56,541
Bhairav.

488
00:31:56,621 --> 00:31:57,181
Sir.

489
00:31:57,301 --> 00:31:59,741
Teach Rajasthani folksongs to Dholu.

490
00:31:59,821 --> 00:32:00,101
Yes.

491
00:32:00,221 --> 00:32:00,541
Uncle.

492
00:32:00,621 --> 00:32:01,621
Sing folk songs.

493
00:32:02,941 --> 00:32:04,381
No. Uncle.

494
00:32:05,501 --> 00:32:06,781
Enough. Enough.

495
00:32:07,301 --> 00:32:08,941
Let her hear the entire song. Okay?

496
00:32:09,861 --> 00:32:11,821
I will just come back. Don't worry.

497
00:32:12,941 --> 00:32:16,781
Dholu, look, he came today after
one and a half years because of you.

498
00:32:16,941 --> 00:32:19,941
Otherwise sir doesn't
venture out of the village.

499
00:33:45,181 --> 00:33:45,621
Sir.

500
00:33:45,741 --> 00:33:46,381
Sir.

501
00:33:46,501 --> 00:33:46,941
Sir.

502
00:33:47,341 --> 00:33:47,941
Sir.

503
00:33:48,101 --> 00:33:48,581
Do something.

504
00:33:48,701 --> 00:33:49,701
Yes.

505
00:33:49,821 --> 00:33:50,821
This sand.

506
00:33:51,181 --> 00:33:52,581
What is this?

507
00:33:52,701 --> 00:33:53,701
Where are we stuck?

508
00:33:54,541 --> 00:33:55,621
Where is the binocular?

509
00:33:58,421 --> 00:33:59,421
Oh God!

510
00:34:01,061 --> 00:34:02,301
Where do we have to go?

511
00:34:02,421 --> 00:34:03,221
Sir, here.

512
00:34:03,341 --> 00:34:03,941
Sir, there.

513
00:34:04,101 --> 00:34:04,421
What?

514
00:34:04,501 --> 00:34:04,941
Sir, here.

515
00:34:05,101 --> 00:34:05,421
Sir, there.

516
00:34:06,181 --> 00:34:09,421
If I depend on you
guys, I will reach Nepal.

517
00:34:10,181 --> 00:34:11,661
Pakistan is that way.

518
00:34:11,741 --> 00:34:12,261
What?

519
00:34:12,501 --> 00:34:13,501
Pakistan is that way.

520
00:34:13,581 --> 00:34:15,701
You fool, Pakistan is in Kashmir.

521
00:34:16,541 --> 00:34:17,541
Come on.

522
00:34:22,261 --> 00:34:24,821
You fool, where did they go?

523
00:34:25,941 --> 00:34:27,861
Come on. Look up.

524
00:34:28,861 --> 00:34:30,941
Why are you carrying the bottle, you moron?

525
00:34:31,061 --> 00:34:32,341
Did I tell you to sleep?

526
00:34:39,581 --> 00:34:42,701
Sir, we will get buried in
the sand, hungry and naked.

527
00:34:42,781 --> 00:34:43,941
Look, vultures are also circling above.

528
00:34:44,101 --> 00:34:47,541
Keep quiet. Keep quiet. Or else I will
bury you here alive without a funeral.

529
00:34:49,101 --> 00:34:50,861
Uncle has already driven me crazy.

530
00:34:51,621 --> 00:34:56,141
I swear. If we get out of here,
I will bury uncle right here.

531
00:34:56,221 --> 00:34:57,301
Beneath the camel.

532
00:34:59,301 --> 00:35:01,901
Sir, speaking of camel, I remembered.

533
00:35:01,941 --> 00:35:03,061
In desert people use camel.

534
00:35:09,421 --> 00:35:11,581
Bend. Bend.

535
00:35:11,661 --> 00:35:12,901
I won't bend. He will bend.

536
00:35:12,941 --> 00:35:13,741
Why should I bend?

537
00:35:13,821 --> 00:35:14,221
Bend.

538
00:35:14,341 --> 00:35:15,741
Why? Do I get salary for this?

539
00:35:15,821 --> 00:35:17,181
Signal.

540
00:35:17,501 --> 00:35:18,381
Bend.

541
00:35:18,461 --> 00:35:19,221
I won't bend.

542
00:35:19,341 --> 00:35:19,781
Bend.

543
00:35:19,901 --> 00:35:21,101
There is sand in my underwear.

544
00:35:21,941 --> 00:35:22,941
Bend.

545
00:35:25,501 --> 00:35:26,501
What is all this?

546
00:35:27,501 --> 00:35:28,101
Why is he doing all this?

547
00:35:28,181 --> 00:35:30,341
Got the signal. Got the signal.

548
00:35:30,461 --> 00:35:32,501
Hey! You scoundrels!

549
00:35:34,901 --> 00:35:39,541
My decision is that
Dalchand will cook for a week

550
00:35:39,661 --> 00:35:40,941
and the wife will eat first.

551
00:35:41,021 --> 00:35:41,861
Well done.

552
00:35:41,941 --> 00:35:47,181
A special thing. I want
you to meet someone.

553
00:35:47,901 --> 00:35:51,621
Dholu. Come here. This is my nephew.

554
00:35:52,381 --> 00:35:54,261
He has come from Mumbai.
Dholu, come here. Come.

555
00:35:54,381 --> 00:35:55,861
Dholu, come here. Come.

556
00:35:57,541 --> 00:35:59,141
Dholu, wish everyone. Wish them.

557
00:36:00,861 --> 00:36:01,501
Hello.

558
00:36:01,581 --> 00:36:02,021
Hello.

559
00:36:02,141 --> 00:36:04,461
Hello. Hello, Mr Dholu. How do you do?

560
00:36:06,861 --> 00:36:07,861
Very good. Thank you.

561
00:36:08,101 --> 00:36:08,461
They speak English.

562
00:36:08,541 --> 00:36:09,061
Uncle...

563
00:36:09,141 --> 00:36:12,301
But Dholu, what do you do?

564
00:36:13,901 --> 00:36:15,381
I manage events.

565
00:36:15,821 --> 00:36:16,381
Event?

566
00:36:16,461 --> 00:36:18,501
We also manage sheep and goats.

567
00:36:18,901 --> 00:36:20,861
I don't understand.

568
00:36:21,301 --> 00:36:22,501
What do you mean?

569
00:36:22,861 --> 00:36:24,061
Do you people watch TV?

570
00:36:24,141 --> 00:36:24,341
Yes.

571
00:36:24,461 --> 00:36:24,741
Yes.

572
00:36:24,861 --> 00:36:25,341
Yes.

573
00:36:25,581 --> 00:36:27,181
The dance shows you see on TV.

574
00:36:27,301 --> 00:36:27,501
Yes.

575
00:36:27,581 --> 00:36:27,941
Yes.

576
00:36:28,061 --> 00:36:30,301
Arranging it. Getting
sponsorships. Nothing much.

577
00:36:30,421 --> 00:36:34,101
I understood the song and
dance. But what is a sponsor?

578
00:36:34,861 --> 00:36:35,901
Tell them.

579
00:36:36,221 --> 00:36:37,221
Okay, tell me something.

580
00:36:37,821 --> 00:36:39,181
Who plans wedding here?

581
00:36:39,301 --> 00:36:40,101
I do.

582
00:36:40,301 --> 00:36:44,061
Do this. On the next full
moon, you'll plan it for free.

583
00:36:44,421 --> 00:36:47,701
Dholu, have I gone
crazy to plan it for free?

584
00:36:51,141 --> 00:36:54,221
In return your name
will appear in bold letters.

585
00:36:54,461 --> 00:36:57,341
Picture too. I mean photo. A big one.

586
00:36:58,421 --> 00:36:59,421
That can happen.

587
00:36:59,861 --> 00:37:01,941
And who'll arrange the food?

588
00:37:02,061 --> 00:37:03,741
Food and liquor is on me.

589
00:37:03,861 --> 00:37:05,141
I don't have that much time.

590
00:37:05,901 --> 00:37:08,181
Pick up uncle by evening
and get the signature.

591
00:37:08,261 --> 00:37:08,581
Okay.

592
00:37:08,781 --> 00:37:11,381
So tell me. What is the program?

593
00:37:12,781 --> 00:37:13,781
Program?

594
00:37:19,621 --> 00:37:21,941
Rajasthan's folk song and dance.

595
00:37:23,261 --> 00:37:26,581
This evening in Shekhawati
will be for Gulabo.

596
00:37:26,941 --> 00:37:28,221
Superb.

597
00:37:28,341 --> 00:37:30,381
Wow. Superb.

598
00:37:31,381 --> 00:37:32,941
They clap for everything.

599
00:37:36,541 --> 00:37:37,821
Take care. Come here.

600
00:37:39,941 --> 00:37:41,221
You have gone mad, Ranvir.

601
00:37:42,061 --> 00:37:42,381
Let's go.

602
00:37:42,501 --> 00:37:45,901
Gulabo will not dance in front
of public in such programs.

603
00:37:46,061 --> 00:37:46,381
That's it.

604
00:37:46,501 --> 00:37:47,221
Father.

605
00:37:47,461 --> 00:37:48,461
Hey, girl.

606
00:37:48,621 --> 00:37:49,941
Uncle, it's for a good cause.

607
00:37:51,021 --> 00:37:52,021
It's the full moon.

608
00:37:52,581 --> 00:37:55,261
Will tourists do the folk dance
of this place if not the locals?

609
00:37:56,021 --> 00:37:58,741
As if you know a lot about the culture here?
- Greetings, aunt.

610
00:37:59,661 --> 00:38:03,341
Have you ever lived in Rajasthan? Mr Dholu.

611
00:38:03,821 --> 00:38:05,261
What is wrong with you?

612
00:38:05,341 --> 00:38:06,461
You are also like me.

613
00:38:07,061 --> 00:38:09,581
You studied abroad.
In fact, you taught them.

614
00:38:10,741 --> 00:38:11,821
So tell me, uncle.

615
00:38:12,501 --> 00:38:15,821
Why did you come here after
earning so much of fame and money?

616
00:38:16,381 --> 00:38:20,941
Tell him, sir. The boy is
asking so sweetly. Tell him.

617
00:38:22,221 --> 00:38:25,541
I was teaching the
foreigners there in Oxford.

618
00:38:27,941 --> 00:38:29,701
You must give back society

619
00:38:30,941 --> 00:38:33,541
because your society
has given you your identity.

620
00:38:35,461 --> 00:38:37,021
Understand your roots.

621
00:38:38,221 --> 00:38:40,341
Respect your culture.

622
00:38:42,461 --> 00:38:46,541
The voice was echoing in
the hall packed with foreigners.

623
00:38:49,221 --> 00:38:52,901
I wonder where this voice came from.

624
00:38:54,381 --> 00:38:59,941
'Madhav Singh, you
yourself never acted on it.'

625
00:39:01,541 --> 00:39:04,901
'When you did you do
what you are teaching?'

626
00:39:07,781 --> 00:39:13,581
And I got it. I packed
my bags. Left everything.

627
00:39:17,261 --> 00:39:20,741
This is quite a good place.
Painting in every house.

628
00:39:21,141 --> 00:39:22,661
I mean it's like yours. Yours is nice.

629
00:39:23,061 --> 00:39:24,621
But where are we going?

630
00:39:27,421 --> 00:39:28,461
Hello.

631
00:39:28,781 --> 00:39:30,261
Hello.

632
00:39:30,341 --> 00:39:31,821
Hello. God bless.

633
00:39:31,941 --> 00:39:35,181
Dholu. My sister Shakuntala's son.

634
00:39:37,501 --> 00:39:40,661
Dholu, seek their blessings. Come on.

635
00:40:03,221 --> 00:40:04,501
Don't trouble me during the match.

636
00:40:04,581 --> 00:40:05,941
Uncle, don't start again. Come, have food.

637
00:40:06,101 --> 00:40:07,061
Yes.

638
00:40:07,141 --> 00:40:07,741
Coming.

639
00:40:07,861 --> 00:40:08,341
Good.

640
00:40:08,421 --> 00:40:09,421
Come.

641
00:40:11,701 --> 00:40:16,461
Have some 'Gatte ki Sabzi'. 'Daal Baati'
is our famous dish. Have one at least.

642
00:40:16,661 --> 00:40:18,221
And give me ghee. Where is the ghee?

643
00:40:18,661 --> 00:40:19,541
Ghee is a must.

644
00:40:19,661 --> 00:40:20,821
Why do you love ghee so much?

645
00:40:21,061 --> 00:40:23,461
You will build muscles,
Ranvir. A little bit.

646
00:40:23,821 --> 00:40:27,101
It will fall. You'll have to eat it.

647
00:40:27,181 --> 00:40:28,181
Okay.

648
00:40:30,821 --> 00:40:31,741
You are good at sketching.

649
00:40:31,821 --> 00:40:32,341
Uncle.

650
00:40:32,701 --> 00:40:33,341
Tell me.

651
00:40:33,581 --> 00:40:37,901
If you come with me to
Mumbai that'll be great fun.

652
00:40:37,941 --> 00:40:38,461
Give it to me.

653
00:40:38,701 --> 00:40:40,501
You'll get a change.

654
00:40:41,301 --> 00:40:41,781
Change?

655
00:40:41,901 --> 00:40:42,901
Yes.

656
00:40:45,301 --> 00:40:46,941
How will going to Mumbai give me a change?

657
00:40:47,621 --> 00:40:51,621
It's a concrete jungle.

658
00:40:52,581 --> 00:40:53,941
It is a concrete jungle. Alright?

659
00:40:54,941 --> 00:40:56,381
Concrete jungle, that's right.

660
00:40:57,701 --> 00:40:59,061
He should be riding the camel.

661
00:40:59,141 --> 00:41:01,861
It's just that... If you'd come to Mumbai,

662
00:41:03,301 --> 00:41:06,861
And sign the no objection
certificate of my mother's plot.

663
00:41:07,101 --> 00:41:09,621
And I could get it transferred.
It will take just 5 minutes.

664
00:41:11,701 --> 00:41:14,181
Here. Go.

665
00:41:14,261 --> 00:41:15,261
Okay.

666
00:41:16,061 --> 00:41:17,221
I'll see you later.

667
00:41:17,581 --> 00:41:18,101
Come on, Gattu.

668
00:41:18,181 --> 00:41:19,821
Dholu, come here.

669
00:41:23,141 --> 00:41:24,141
Look,

670
00:41:26,141 --> 00:41:31,101
history has been a witness that land
and property create rift between brothers.

671
00:41:32,261 --> 00:41:36,301
With God's grace, there is a
special thing about our family.

672
00:41:36,901 --> 00:41:38,341
And that is trust.

673
00:41:38,901 --> 00:41:39,901
Uncle.

674
00:41:40,181 --> 00:41:43,061
That is your land. This
is a Rajput's promise.

675
00:41:43,381 --> 00:41:44,101
Gul, the tea...

676
00:41:44,221 --> 00:41:45,221
Uncle.

677
00:41:48,181 --> 00:41:50,901
Look, you are really educated. I agree.

678
00:41:50,941 --> 00:41:54,621
But promises don't mean
anything in the cities.

679
00:41:59,141 --> 00:42:01,701
There is a builder named
Kukreja. He is really big.

680
00:42:03,461 --> 00:42:04,861
He wants to grab the property.

681
00:42:05,261 --> 00:42:06,621
And since 8 months, I have been...

682
00:42:08,581 --> 00:42:10,941
Please try to understand my
situation. It is not good, uncle.

683
00:42:23,381 --> 00:42:25,181
Let me tell you something,

684
00:42:27,381 --> 00:42:29,141
and it's very important.

685
00:42:30,581 --> 00:42:32,581
A man who fights for his land

686
00:42:33,581 --> 00:42:35,621
is a true blue Rajput.

687
00:42:38,341 --> 00:42:39,341
I didn't get you.

688
00:42:41,141 --> 00:42:43,901
You will understand
everything when the time comes.

689
00:42:44,901 --> 00:42:48,501
Gul, don't worry.

690
00:42:49,661 --> 00:42:52,221
This is just a couple as such.

691
00:42:53,341 --> 00:42:58,101
But the real meaning is in your blood.

692
00:42:59,301 --> 00:43:01,621
You'll understand when the time comes.

693
00:43:04,381 --> 00:43:08,501
We ate worth Rs 150. You ate
food worth Rs 80 and I worth Rs 75.

694
00:43:08,741 --> 00:43:08,901
Okay.

695
00:43:08,941 --> 00:43:10,541
So Rs 150 plus Rs 75, makes it Rs 200.

696
00:43:10,621 --> 00:43:13,501
Where did Rs 250 go? You've
done this addition previously as well.

697
00:43:13,901 --> 00:43:15,821
You studied Maths till
the eighth grade, right?

698
00:43:17,141 --> 00:43:19,861
Because Rs 70, Rs 80, Rs 90...

699
00:43:19,941 --> 00:43:20,621
Yes. What is it?

700
00:43:20,821 --> 00:43:24,141
Sir, I just saw everyone leaving.

701
00:43:24,781 --> 00:43:28,101
We won't get a better
chance to kidnap the uncle.

702
00:43:28,181 --> 00:43:33,381
Uncle is home alone. That's great.

703
00:43:33,741 --> 00:43:35,861
We'll come to do away with his loneliness.

704
00:43:45,741 --> 00:43:47,421
Hello. Welcome.

705
00:44:15,341 --> 00:44:16,941
Have you ever thought
about becoming an actress?

706
00:44:17,101 --> 00:44:18,261
Darn it.

707
00:44:20,181 --> 00:44:22,621
Actress? I am not crazy.

708
00:44:23,541 --> 00:44:24,541
Crazy?

709
00:44:26,421 --> 00:44:27,661
Then think a little crazily.

710
00:44:28,581 --> 00:44:31,261
Think big. Get out of this place.

711
00:44:31,341 --> 00:44:34,461
And take Bollywood by storm.

712
00:44:35,141 --> 00:44:37,941
That's it. Tell uncle that you
want to come to Mumbai with me.

713
00:44:38,941 --> 00:44:42,941
No. I am sorry. Father says you have to
become corrupt before you become an actress.

714
00:44:44,221 --> 00:44:46,701
No. No. It's not that.
You have a wrong notion.

715
00:44:47,581 --> 00:44:48,941
What?

716
00:44:49,061 --> 00:44:50,381
You have a wrong family.

717
00:44:50,741 --> 00:44:53,381
Your father. He is
telling you wrong things.

718
00:45:01,701 --> 00:45:03,381
Do you really think that I dance well?

719
00:45:07,381 --> 00:45:10,341
Okay. So you guys are kidnapping me?

720
00:45:10,941 --> 00:45:11,621
Hello. Hello.

721
00:45:11,701 --> 00:45:12,821
Hello.

722
00:45:13,301 --> 00:45:18,901
Look, tell me when you feel right as to
who are you and where are you taking me?

723
00:45:19,661 --> 00:45:20,821
Hello. Hello, uncle.

724
00:45:20,941 --> 00:45:22,101
God bless. No worries.

725
00:45:22,221 --> 00:45:24,021
He is bigger than police. He is our uncle.

726
00:45:24,421 --> 00:45:25,181
Yes, he is right.

727
00:45:25,261 --> 00:45:27,021
Today all the problems will be over.

728
00:45:27,341 --> 00:45:29,461
And Kukreja will become builder number one.

729
00:45:29,861 --> 00:45:31,861
How is the business of kidnapping?

730
00:45:32,381 --> 00:45:34,701
Do you do any other business
in your spare time or no?

731
00:45:35,421 --> 00:45:37,141
Who is the leader? Are you the one?

732
00:45:37,261 --> 00:45:39,261
Keep quiet. Shut him up.

733
00:45:39,701 --> 00:45:41,421
We have kidnapped
him. But he is torturing us.

734
00:45:41,541 --> 00:45:42,061
No.

735
00:45:42,181 --> 00:45:43,061
Gag him. Gag him.

736
00:45:43,141 --> 00:45:44,141
Show me your hand.

737
00:45:44,261 --> 00:45:45,781
Get lost, uncle.

738
00:45:48,701 --> 00:45:53,101
Jalebi Bai. Jalebi Bai.

739
00:45:53,221 --> 00:45:54,061
Let's go.

740
00:45:54,181 --> 00:45:55,381
You go alone.

741
00:45:55,941 --> 00:45:59,181
What did I tell you? Out with my Rs 125.

742
00:45:59,661 --> 00:46:01,221
What do I say, Parikh?

743
00:46:01,901 --> 00:46:03,181
I don't have much money either.

744
00:46:03,421 --> 00:46:04,821
That's why I suggest you buy it now.

745
00:46:04,941 --> 00:46:06,461
Now is the time.

746
00:46:06,741 --> 00:46:08,381
I don't understand what I should buy.

747
00:46:09,101 --> 00:46:11,501
Buy fertilizer. Fertilizer.

748
00:46:13,141 --> 00:46:14,621
Girl, would you like to eat something?

749
00:46:14,741 --> 00:46:14,941
No.

750
00:46:15,101 --> 00:46:15,541
Parikh.

751
00:46:15,821 --> 00:46:16,221
Yes.

752
00:46:16,901 --> 00:46:18,061
Parikh, buy fertilizer.

753
00:46:18,661 --> 00:46:19,661
Fertilizer?

754
00:46:19,901 --> 00:46:20,581
Yes. Fertilizer.

755
00:46:20,781 --> 00:46:21,781
Alright.

756
00:46:24,261 --> 00:46:25,621
I am buying it on your suggestion.

757
00:46:25,861 --> 00:46:28,581
You win all the bets, right.
You must have got a tip.

758
00:46:28,661 --> 00:46:31,621
Waiters get tips, dear.

759
00:46:31,941 --> 00:46:34,421
My words never fail me.

760
00:46:34,901 --> 00:46:36,541
And look, there will
be rain. Crops will grow.

761
00:46:36,621 --> 00:46:37,621
Grow.

762
00:46:37,901 --> 00:46:38,501
Yes.

763
00:46:38,821 --> 00:46:40,821
Bulls will take a dump.
So fertilizer will sell.

764
00:46:41,541 --> 00:46:44,061
It means there will be bounty
of crops this time in the market.

765
00:46:47,541 --> 00:46:50,381
Uncle, I need a small
sweet signature from you.

766
00:46:50,621 --> 00:46:51,621
On this paper.

767
00:46:51,861 --> 00:46:52,941
What signature?

768
00:46:53,421 --> 00:46:54,421
What paper?

769
00:46:54,861 --> 00:46:55,861
No. Nothing.

770
00:47:01,661 --> 00:47:02,581
Uncle.

771
00:47:02,741 --> 00:47:03,741
Yes, you bug?

772
00:47:03,861 --> 00:47:05,301
Are you going to sign it or not?

773
00:47:05,821 --> 00:47:07,261
No.

774
00:47:07,861 --> 00:47:11,061
Sir, uncle can't sign even if he wants to.

775
00:47:11,941 --> 00:47:14,901
He is buried in sand. I mean in the soil.

776
00:47:15,821 --> 00:47:17,221
I also know that.

777
00:47:19,581 --> 00:47:23,221
- Uncle, you won't sign it?
- No.

778
00:47:24,941 --> 00:47:27,861
Alright. Great. Let us go.

779
00:47:27,941 --> 00:47:29,141
Go. Alright.

780
00:47:29,421 --> 00:47:32,421
Uncle, don't trouble the snakes
and scorpions that come here.

781
00:47:32,501 --> 00:47:33,181
No.

782
00:47:33,421 --> 00:47:35,341
Do you see those vultures circling above?

783
00:47:36,141 --> 00:47:40,661
If they peck you, rip your
flesh, then don't scream. Okay.

784
00:47:40,781 --> 00:47:41,301
Don't worry.

785
00:47:41,421 --> 00:47:45,261
Because there is a desert rule.
Fittest of the survival. Alright?

786
00:47:45,381 --> 00:47:46,381
Alright.

787
00:47:48,061 --> 00:47:50,061
Take care of uncle.

788
00:47:50,781 --> 00:47:55,021
Let's go. Let's take a walk for 15 minutes
and come back. He'll sign immediately.

789
00:47:57,821 --> 00:48:00,221
What happened?

790
00:48:00,461 --> 00:48:03,421
Forget it. Forget it.
Let's go on foot. Forget it.

791
00:48:04,941 --> 00:48:08,261
Where is it? Where are the huge tyre marks?

792
00:48:09,821 --> 00:48:11,461
Where do we have to go?

793
00:48:12,421 --> 00:48:12,781
There.

794
00:48:12,861 --> 00:48:13,861
There.

795
00:48:14,461 --> 00:48:18,701
South pole. North pole.
Put your hands down. Down.

796
00:48:22,461 --> 00:48:26,901
Uncle. Uncle, we are back.
I don't feel like leaving you.

797
00:48:30,061 --> 00:48:32,181
Don't you have anything
else to do? Good for nothing.

798
00:48:34,581 --> 00:48:36,381
The plan of the signature
has been cancelled.

799
00:48:36,581 --> 00:48:40,421
Do us a favour. Show
us the way out of here.

800
00:48:41,541 --> 00:48:45,301
Useless. Change the path of your life.

801
00:48:46,141 --> 00:48:47,941
And you'll find the right way.

802
00:48:50,301 --> 00:48:53,221
Uncle, please. Please try to understand.

803
00:48:53,301 --> 00:48:56,701
We have no other way. Except
that you show us the way.

804
00:48:56,901 --> 00:48:57,901
I know.

805
00:48:58,301 --> 00:49:02,141
Please. Get us out of this sea of sand.

806
00:49:08,021 --> 00:49:10,301
Goodness counts for nothing these days.

807
00:49:11,501 --> 00:49:15,341
Uncle, look at him. He
has two lovely wives.

808
00:49:15,541 --> 00:49:17,381
Four small children.

809
00:49:17,941 --> 00:49:20,061
Uncle, if you don't show us the way

810
00:49:21,941 --> 00:49:24,501
then his family happy will be ruined.

811
00:49:25,141 --> 00:49:26,861
Hey this is not funny.

812
00:49:26,941 --> 00:49:30,221
Funny? You think this
is a joke? This is a joke?

813
00:49:30,341 --> 00:49:34,661
Help me. Uncle, please help me.

814
00:49:36,021 --> 00:49:39,781
Why are you so upset? You thought I'd
shoot you? No way. You are my brother.

815
00:49:44,301 --> 00:49:46,821
Does he think he is some great saint?

816
00:49:55,581 --> 00:49:58,141
This is it. This is it. Enough.

817
00:50:03,821 --> 00:50:05,501
What happened?

818
00:50:05,581 --> 00:50:10,901
Friends, in the desert,
it is survival of the fittest.

819
00:50:20,221 --> 00:50:24,741
This is so beautiful. I'll be dancing here?

820
00:50:25,101 --> 00:50:26,101
Yes.

821
00:50:27,061 --> 00:50:28,421
These are the girls of my village.

822
00:50:30,661 --> 00:50:32,941
Great. Great job.

823
00:50:33,541 --> 00:50:35,301
You have created an oasis in the desert.

824
00:50:35,421 --> 00:50:36,821
Will you have some milk?

825
00:50:37,141 --> 00:50:38,141
Oh no.

826
00:50:39,541 --> 00:50:40,661
My big picture.

827
00:50:41,181 --> 00:50:42,301
Radhe Shyam.

828
00:50:42,421 --> 00:50:42,941
Yes?

829
00:50:43,061 --> 00:50:45,861
Gul Gule Gulistan. See this, Bhairav.

830
00:50:45,941 --> 00:50:51,541
Yes, dear. One minute. Where is the speaker and the
curtains? Where is everything? What is all this?

831
00:50:58,941 --> 00:51:03,341
Presenting to you the pride of Rajasthan.

832
00:51:03,781 --> 00:51:08,501
And the future actress.
Gul, Gule, Gulistan.

833
00:51:09,021 --> 00:51:11,221
Gulabo aka Gul.

834
00:51:18,541 --> 00:51:20,941
Wow. Mind blowing.

835
00:51:38,941 --> 00:51:39,941
Check it out.

836
00:52:14,181 --> 00:52:17,741
'You'll have to understand
what I am about to tell you.'

837
00:52:18,181 --> 00:52:19,421
'Go ahead, dear.'

838
00:52:20,301 --> 00:52:21,941
'I want to go to Mumbai.'

839
00:52:23,061 --> 00:52:26,941
'Dear, is there already less crowd there?
That you are going to add to the crowd.'

840
00:52:27,341 --> 00:52:29,541
'I want to make a name
for myself in that crowd.'

841
00:52:30,381 --> 00:52:32,941
'I want to make a name. Do something big.'

842
00:52:38,541 --> 00:52:43,461
Uncle, come on, smile. Forget it. Enjoy it.

843
00:52:49,301 --> 00:52:52,101
'Gul, I understood what you said.'

844
00:52:53,381 --> 00:52:53,901
'Go. Go to Mumbai.'

845
00:52:53,941 --> 00:52:55,021
'Really?'

846
00:52:55,621 --> 00:52:56,701
'Don't worry.'

847
00:52:57,581 --> 00:52:59,021
'But I have a condition.'

848
00:52:59,941 --> 00:53:00,941
'What?'

849
00:53:02,661 --> 00:53:03,941
'I'll also come with you.'

850
00:53:09,941 --> 00:53:12,061
'I'll go to Mumbai in my car.'

851
00:53:12,261 --> 00:53:13,381
'We'll go to Mumbai in this?'

852
00:53:13,501 --> 00:53:14,501
'Yes. Yes.'

853
00:53:14,621 --> 00:53:15,821
'I am not travelling in this.'

854
00:53:17,461 --> 00:53:18,701
'Mumbai trip cancelled.'

855
00:53:18,781 --> 00:53:19,301
'Father. Please agree.'

856
00:53:19,421 --> 00:53:20,341
'Okay. Okay.'

857
00:53:20,461 --> 00:53:21,461
'Please agree.'

858
00:53:21,661 --> 00:53:22,661
'As you say.'

859
00:54:56,501 --> 00:54:58,421
Hello. Hello, Mr Lal.
There are still 12 days left.

860
00:54:58,541 --> 00:55:01,581
Hello. What? Hello. Ranvir.

861
00:55:02,221 --> 00:55:04,181
I will do it.

862
00:55:04,261 --> 00:55:06,781
It is all set.

863
00:55:18,941 --> 00:55:23,941
Dholu. We have reached Mumbai.

864
00:55:24,541 --> 00:55:27,941
It is so bright. And it
is so crowded as well.

865
00:55:31,581 --> 00:55:36,741
All hail Lord Ganesh.
So Dholu, you live here?

866
00:55:37,821 --> 00:55:38,821
Here.

867
00:55:39,381 --> 00:55:40,941
I'll take the stairs.

868
00:55:41,101 --> 00:55:42,101
What?

869
00:55:42,301 --> 00:55:43,941
I'll go with the girl.

870
00:55:44,581 --> 00:55:45,581
But this...

871
00:55:46,741 --> 00:55:48,101
This is a lift.

872
00:55:48,181 --> 00:55:49,181
Uncle...

873
00:55:49,541 --> 00:55:51,381
Bhairav! Darn it!

874
00:55:51,501 --> 00:55:53,341
Life means to keep moving.

875
00:55:54,301 --> 00:55:56,221
Uncle, our forefathers
were not hill dwellers.

876
00:55:56,941 --> 00:55:58,341
But they were apes.

877
00:55:58,621 --> 00:56:00,381
Hello. Uncle.

878
00:56:05,581 --> 00:56:09,381
Eat. Eat.

879
00:56:14,221 --> 00:56:16,261
You are city birds. Talk in English.

880
00:56:23,261 --> 00:56:27,541
No. No. Let me do it. Okay.

881
00:56:27,661 --> 00:56:29,821
Let me do it.

882
00:56:30,181 --> 00:56:31,181
- Do it.
- But I...

883
00:56:32,101 --> 00:56:32,621
Darn it!

884
00:56:32,901 --> 00:56:35,941
Dholu, do all these
girls live in this city?

885
00:56:36,421 --> 00:56:36,821
No.

886
00:56:36,901 --> 00:56:38,901
What girls?

887
00:56:39,101 --> 00:56:40,861
These aren't mine.

888
00:56:40,941 --> 00:56:41,581
So whose are they?

889
00:56:41,661 --> 00:56:42,861
Mr Lal's.

890
00:56:42,941 --> 00:56:47,221
So what did Mr Lal think?
You need them more?

891
00:56:47,341 --> 00:56:47,941
You dog!

892
00:56:48,061 --> 00:56:50,101
Listen. Return the pages at least.

893
00:56:52,141 --> 00:56:53,741
Like this.

894
00:56:56,221 --> 00:56:57,421
Like this.

895
00:57:02,141 --> 00:57:03,141
Like this.

896
00:57:05,341 --> 00:57:06,341
What are these?

897
00:57:07,821 --> 00:57:08,821
Clothes.

898
00:57:09,501 --> 00:57:10,061
For you.

899
00:57:10,461 --> 00:57:11,621
This...

900
00:57:12,221 --> 00:57:15,141
I have to take you day
after tomorrow. So be ready.

901
00:57:15,941 --> 00:57:18,141
Ready? Where do you want to take me?

902
00:57:18,941 --> 00:57:24,661
A true Rajput warrior always blah
blah. Always keeps his promise.

903
00:57:25,821 --> 00:57:29,541
I told you that you had talent.
I will take you to Mumbai.

904
00:57:30,461 --> 00:57:31,501
Well, what I said...

905
00:57:31,581 --> 00:57:35,861
Darn you. Dholu. Look.

906
00:57:36,181 --> 00:57:36,821
What happened?

907
00:57:36,941 --> 00:57:39,061
How do you sit on this? How?

908
00:57:39,181 --> 00:57:40,221
That is not how you are...

909
00:57:40,381 --> 00:57:40,901
Hello, Ranvir.

910
00:57:40,941 --> 00:57:42,261
Yes, Mr Lal.

911
00:57:42,661 --> 00:57:45,381
That rascal has started construction
at the site. Hold on, will you?

912
00:57:45,461 --> 00:57:46,701
You better cut the call right away.

913
00:57:46,821 --> 00:57:47,221
What?

914
00:57:47,301 --> 00:57:48,821
Bulldozer? Hold on.

915
00:57:48,941 --> 00:57:51,621
Bulldozer. I am coming there. Wait.

916
00:57:57,541 --> 00:57:59,701
No. Stop.

917
00:58:00,101 --> 00:58:01,701
Hey, stop it.

918
00:58:05,141 --> 00:58:07,141
That's a real hero.

919
00:58:09,461 --> 00:58:12,901
Anyone who messes
with me will be destroyed.

920
00:58:12,941 --> 00:58:15,061
Be it a bulldozer.

921
00:58:21,661 --> 00:58:23,901
Myself Cookie Kukreja.

922
00:58:28,621 --> 00:58:29,621
Ranvir.

923
00:58:31,421 --> 00:58:32,421
Ranvir?

924
00:58:32,581 --> 00:58:33,581
Yes.

925
00:58:33,741 --> 00:58:37,301
Ranvir, since you are here.
I would like to talk to you.

926
00:58:38,141 --> 00:58:43,541
Come to my palace. Come on. You are
my brother. We'll sit up and chat. Come on.

927
00:58:46,941 --> 00:58:50,181
Come along. Even our morning walk is done.

928
00:58:51,581 --> 00:58:57,261
Look at this. This is
called fresh air. Come on.

929
00:58:57,381 --> 00:58:58,541
Why have you brought me here?

930
00:58:59,901 --> 00:59:03,941
Don't worry. I will neither push
you nor betray you. Come on.

931
00:59:18,021 --> 00:59:19,941
Come on. Come on. Grab me.

932
00:59:22,941 --> 00:59:24,461
Come on.

933
00:59:25,141 --> 00:59:27,941
Don't be scared. Lie down. Lie down.

934
00:59:29,021 --> 00:59:31,621
Your own building looks so nice
when you look at it from down there.

935
00:59:31,701 --> 00:59:33,021
It looks scary from above.

936
00:59:34,341 --> 00:59:36,941
Look at that. The heights. Tall buildings.

937
00:59:37,701 --> 00:59:38,701
Now look down.

938
00:59:39,781 --> 00:59:42,221
What is that? Shakuntala Niwas.

939
00:59:42,901 --> 00:59:44,341
A small bird's nest.

940
00:59:46,581 --> 00:59:49,861
The rest have gone so far
ahead. And he is still where he was.

941
00:59:51,661 --> 00:59:52,861
Don't you see his pain?

942
00:59:53,941 --> 00:59:56,861
I can. He cries every night.

943
00:59:57,221 --> 01:00:00,421
Kukreja, I also want to touch the sky.

944
01:00:00,781 --> 01:00:03,501
I also want someone to jump
by a parachute from my roof.

945
01:00:06,141 --> 01:00:08,261
So that's why I say
that join hands with me.

946
01:00:09,701 --> 01:00:11,421
You solve a small problem of mine.

947
01:00:12,141 --> 01:00:13,621
I will make sure you benefit greatly.

948
01:00:14,581 --> 01:00:15,781
I will give you Rs 30 million.

949
01:00:19,061 --> 01:00:20,061
So is the deal on?

950
01:00:20,941 --> 01:00:21,941
Done.

951
01:00:23,221 --> 01:00:24,221
Listen.

952
01:00:27,141 --> 01:00:28,061
Hey, what are you doing?

953
01:00:28,141 --> 01:00:29,141
But...

954
01:00:30,181 --> 01:00:31,221
But not for Rs 30 million.

955
01:00:31,301 --> 01:00:31,901
Then?

956
01:00:32,101 --> 01:00:33,101
250

957
01:00:35,741 --> 01:00:39,781
Actually Mr Kukreja, the
rate of dowry has gone up.

958
01:00:42,221 --> 01:00:44,941
So is the deal on?

959
01:00:47,181 --> 01:00:48,181
Let go.

960
01:00:49,621 --> 01:00:54,581
People keep ringing bells all the time.
People don't ring temple bells so much.

961
01:00:54,661 --> 01:00:55,421
Yes. Welcome.

962
01:00:55,501 --> 01:00:56,221
What is this?

963
01:00:56,301 --> 01:00:57,341
What?

964
01:00:58,221 --> 01:01:01,181
Who are you? Call the boy who lives here.

965
01:01:01,461 --> 01:01:03,701
Okay. Okay. You are Ranvir's
friend. Welcome. Welcome.

966
01:01:03,821 --> 01:01:05,901
I am the secretary.

967
01:01:06,381 --> 01:01:08,941
Ranvir didn't tell me that he
has hired a secretary as well.

968
01:01:09,061 --> 01:01:13,261
Not his. I am this building's
secretary. I am your neighbour.

969
01:01:13,341 --> 01:01:15,941
You can't roam around naked like this.

970
01:01:16,101 --> 01:01:17,901
Welcome. Welcome.

971
01:01:18,221 --> 01:01:22,221
I am Ranvir's uncle. Madhav Singh Rathore.

972
01:01:22,341 --> 01:01:23,781
I've come from Rajasthan.
Come in. Let's have a cup of tea.

973
01:01:23,861 --> 01:01:25,501
I am Swatantra Bharat Bhushan.

974
01:01:25,621 --> 01:01:26,381
Nice name.

975
01:01:26,501 --> 01:01:30,301
I don't have time for
tea. And what is all this?

976
01:01:30,421 --> 01:01:30,861
Painting.

977
01:01:31,061 --> 01:01:34,261
This building has been
painted with the society fund.

978
01:01:34,501 --> 01:01:36,941
Painting on it is prohibited. Get it?

979
01:01:37,461 --> 01:01:41,941
Send Ranvir to the
society office immediately.

980
01:01:42,221 --> 01:01:43,501
To report. One more thing.

981
01:01:44,461 --> 01:01:47,661
This is gross... This is vulgarity.

982
01:01:48,141 --> 01:01:51,661
Moreover, destroying
society property. Disgusting.

983
01:02:40,461 --> 01:02:45,101
Small plants. Small
scissors. Small temples.

984
01:02:45,501 --> 01:02:48,661
Small Gods. Small venerations. Small...

985
01:02:51,301 --> 01:02:54,381
Darn you. Girl, what you have you worn?

986
01:02:56,301 --> 01:02:56,741
Come on.

987
01:02:56,861 --> 01:02:58,341
Small clothes.

988
01:02:58,461 --> 01:03:01,661
Bhairav, come on. We'll
be late for the audition.

989
01:03:01,781 --> 01:03:02,901
Come on, let's go.

990
01:03:11,301 --> 01:03:13,661
Tell Nissan not to move from there.

991
01:03:13,941 --> 01:03:16,021
And ask others to follow him on the bike.

992
01:03:16,141 --> 01:03:17,821
Ask Diwakar to...

993
01:03:17,901 --> 01:03:20,861
Darn it. What's with the
name of goons these days?

994
01:03:21,341 --> 01:03:23,741
Boss, all is good. Everyone
has taken their positions.

995
01:03:24,341 --> 01:03:28,541
Yes, boss. He is twirling
his moustaches right now.

996
01:03:29,061 --> 01:03:30,381
Uncle is coming this way.

997
01:03:30,461 --> 01:03:31,461
Stop the commentary.

998
01:03:31,701 --> 01:03:32,741
And give me the live feed.

999
01:03:32,901 --> 01:03:33,421
Okay.

1000
01:03:33,621 --> 01:03:34,741
The car is approaching, sir.

1001
01:03:36,341 --> 01:03:39,421
He is still dancing. Hey, hit him.

1002
01:03:42,821 --> 01:03:46,141
The car slipped. And he missed, sir.

1003
01:03:46,221 --> 01:03:47,941
Missed him? Missed him.

1004
01:03:48,021 --> 01:03:50,181
You couldn't hit such a
small man with such a big car.

1005
01:03:50,541 --> 01:03:52,661
You are good for nothing.

1006
01:03:52,941 --> 01:03:54,901
I wish you had been run over by that car.

1007
01:03:55,541 --> 01:03:56,541
Missed him.

1008
01:03:56,941 --> 01:03:58,701
Was there a banana skin on the road?

1009
01:03:58,781 --> 01:03:59,381
Yes.

1010
01:03:59,701 --> 01:04:00,701
What is he doing?

1011
01:04:01,461 --> 01:04:04,621
Uncle is looking around like a maniac, sir.

1012
01:04:04,861 --> 01:04:09,061
Maniac. Maniac. Listen to me.

1013
01:04:09,181 --> 01:04:09,581
Yes.

1014
01:04:09,741 --> 01:04:12,541
Rush to the nearby police station.

1015
01:04:12,701 --> 01:04:15,661
And tell them that uncle
has caused this accident.

1016
01:04:15,861 --> 01:04:17,341
And tell them that he is a maniac.

1017
01:04:17,781 --> 01:04:20,581
He should either be in the police
station or at the mental asylum.

1018
01:04:20,741 --> 01:04:21,741
Okay. Okay.

1019
01:04:24,261 --> 01:04:24,701
One!

1020
01:04:25,261 --> 01:04:25,621
Hi.

1021
01:04:25,701 --> 01:04:26,221
Hi.

1022
01:04:26,341 --> 01:04:27,541
Hey, Arjun.

1023
01:04:38,541 --> 01:04:40,941
Hello. Hello.

1024
01:04:48,261 --> 01:04:51,461
I'll get Gul auditioned.
You stay right here.

1025
01:04:56,901 --> 01:04:57,901
No. I will not be able to dance here.

1026
01:04:57,941 --> 01:04:59,301
It's all good, Gul.

1027
01:05:00,061 --> 01:05:04,741
There are so many people here. This is really
weird. I will not be able to do it. And this...

1028
01:05:04,901 --> 01:05:05,901
Wait...

1029
01:05:07,541 --> 01:05:10,421
What are you doing? One minute.

1030
01:05:11,781 --> 01:05:13,741
Until today, only I was your fan, right?
- But...

1031
01:05:14,941 --> 01:05:17,501
I promise. You go inside and dance.

1032
01:05:18,101 --> 01:05:20,581
All of them will become
your fan in 5 minutes.

1033
01:05:22,101 --> 01:05:24,781
So you need not fear. I am right here.

1034
01:05:25,941 --> 01:05:26,941
Okay?

1035
01:05:27,261 --> 01:05:28,261
Yes.

1036
01:05:31,621 --> 01:05:32,621
You?

1037
01:05:33,421 --> 01:05:34,421
What are you doing here?

1038
01:05:34,821 --> 01:05:35,821
This is Gul.

1039
01:05:36,341 --> 01:05:37,821
I have brought her here for audition.

1040
01:05:40,061 --> 01:05:44,181
This is the only job you can do now.

1041
01:05:44,821 --> 01:05:49,421
You beguile girls, show them
big dreams bring them here

1042
01:05:50,261 --> 01:05:51,461
and get them auditioned.

1043
01:05:51,581 --> 01:05:52,341
You...

1044
01:05:52,461 --> 01:05:54,941
You need courage to dream.

1045
01:05:55,421 --> 01:05:58,221
And you need just a
sharp tongue to talk trash.

1046
01:05:58,341 --> 01:06:01,421
Someone might have explained this
before. But you didn't get it, did you?

1047
01:06:01,661 --> 01:06:04,461
Because you have no brains.

1048
01:06:04,861 --> 01:06:06,541
Come on, Ranvir. Move.

1049
01:06:08,421 --> 01:06:09,421
Superb.

1050
01:06:19,501 --> 01:06:20,221
Can we start please?

1051
01:06:20,501 --> 01:06:21,501
One minute please.

1052
01:06:22,261 --> 01:06:23,261
Come on.

1053
01:06:39,101 --> 01:06:40,661
Let's go, Bhairav.

1054
01:06:40,741 --> 01:06:45,301
'There has been a horrific accident.'

1055
01:06:45,861 --> 01:06:50,941
'It is said that an old man
has caused this accident'.

1056
01:06:51,101 --> 01:06:51,541
Father.

1057
01:06:51,941 --> 01:06:52,661
Oh God!

1058
01:06:52,741 --> 01:06:54,541
We let him go out for the first time and...

1059
01:06:54,941 --> 01:06:55,541
Ranvir, this...

1060
01:06:55,621 --> 01:06:56,621
And he got arrested.

1061
01:06:56,781 --> 01:06:57,781
Let's go. Hurry up!

1062
01:06:58,621 --> 01:07:00,061
Come on, Gul. Come on.

1063
01:07:03,781 --> 01:07:05,421
'Oshiwara Police Station.'

1064
01:07:06,141 --> 01:07:06,941
Sir.

1065
01:07:07,101 --> 01:07:09,501
Father.

1066
01:07:10,061 --> 01:07:10,461
Sir.

1067
01:07:10,581 --> 01:07:10,901
Father.

1068
01:07:11,221 --> 01:07:12,741
I am sorry.

1069
01:07:13,901 --> 01:07:14,301
Father.

1070
01:07:14,381 --> 01:07:14,941
Sir.
One minute.

1071
01:07:15,061 --> 01:07:16,061
Father, listen.

1072
01:07:18,941 --> 01:07:19,781
Oh, Mr Singh.

1073
01:07:19,941 --> 01:07:20,941
Yes.

1074
01:07:21,461 --> 01:07:22,461
Mr Singh,

1075
01:07:23,661 --> 01:07:26,781
your uncle has gone insane.

1076
01:07:28,341 --> 01:07:28,661
What...

1077
01:07:28,781 --> 01:07:32,861
You need to get his mental state
checked. So we'll keep him in custody.

1078
01:07:32,941 --> 01:07:34,141
Mentally unstable. Are you...

1079
01:07:34,501 --> 01:07:36,941
Look, he is a very well
respected and educated man.

1080
01:07:37,701 --> 01:07:38,741
Look Mr Singh...

1081
01:07:39,221 --> 01:07:41,781
Educated people fall victim to madness.

1082
01:07:42,821 --> 01:07:46,221
He has testified.

1083
01:07:46,821 --> 01:07:51,141
He has testified. He was getting
a hair cut in Sakhi Hair Salon.

1084
01:07:51,461 --> 01:07:52,261
Right, Prem?

1085
01:07:52,501 --> 01:07:52,901
Yes.

1086
01:07:53,141 --> 01:07:54,381
And we have checked with them.

1087
01:07:54,821 --> 01:07:59,661
And he has given witness that your
uncle stopped in the middle of the road.

1088
01:07:59,941 --> 01:08:03,421
And started dancing in the middle of the
street listening to a song on his headphone.

1089
01:08:03,941 --> 01:08:07,141
Look, uncle. It's Saturday
today. And it's Sunday tomorrow.

1090
01:08:07,501 --> 01:08:09,181
If you don't say anything, how will I...

1091
01:08:11,941 --> 01:08:14,941
It's Saturday. He
doesn't talk on Saturdays.

1092
01:08:15,541 --> 01:08:16,701
He won't talk.

1093
01:08:18,061 --> 01:08:22,221
'A horrific accident happened in
Oshiwara today. The damage was heavy.'

1094
01:08:22,301 --> 01:08:24,821
We shouldn't have come
to Mumbai. Father was right.

1095
01:08:25,501 --> 01:08:26,901
We should've never listened to you.

1096
01:08:26,941 --> 01:08:29,461
'It is said that this man's
mental state is not right.'

1097
01:08:29,661 --> 01:08:32,741
'Through the CCTV
footage in Bright Electronics'

1098
01:08:32,941 --> 01:08:36,581
'we want to ask you as to who
is responsible for this accident.'

1099
01:08:36,781 --> 01:08:38,621
'Is that man really mad?'

1100
01:08:39,501 --> 01:08:41,941
'Terrorists were the only
threat to this city until today.'

1101
01:08:42,101 --> 01:08:43,181
Oh yes.

1102
01:08:43,261 --> 01:08:46,101
'We need to check with our correspondent.'

1103
01:08:46,221 --> 01:08:48,461
What has got you so excited?

1104
01:08:48,701 --> 01:08:50,941
This is Mumbai. There
are cameras everywhere.

1105
01:08:51,261 --> 01:08:52,941
Everything will be clear tomorrow. Yes.

1106
01:09:02,941 --> 01:09:04,901
Sir, we found this from
the shop's recording.

1107
01:09:11,421 --> 01:09:16,821
This footage shows that this
accident happened due to this car.

1108
01:09:16,901 --> 01:09:17,901
Yes.

1109
01:09:18,101 --> 01:09:22,821
We'll have to evict him and
his mad uncle out of the society.

1110
01:09:23,101 --> 01:09:25,341
Do you understand?
We'll have to evict them.

1111
01:09:25,461 --> 01:09:29,581
He roams around in the society naked.
What effect will this have on our society?

1112
01:09:29,661 --> 01:09:34,941
And his nephew was caught
bribing on national television.

1113
01:09:35,501 --> 01:09:37,741
Think of the devil and devil is here.

1114
01:09:38,141 --> 01:09:40,621
Come here all of you. Quick.

1115
01:09:41,381 --> 01:09:44,261
Members, this is the
person I was talking about.

1116
01:09:44,621 --> 01:09:47,021
He should be thrown out
of the society immediately.

1117
01:09:55,181 --> 01:10:00,741
Lord, forgive them for
they know not what they do.

1118
01:10:23,941 --> 01:10:24,941
Sir.

1119
01:10:37,381 --> 01:10:38,421
What did you see?

1120
01:10:42,821 --> 01:10:43,821
Nothing, sir.

1121
01:10:47,581 --> 01:10:49,821
Come to the point. Why did
you come in without knocking?

1122
01:10:50,341 --> 01:10:54,461
I had entered uncle's
mansion after those people left.

1123
01:10:54,621 --> 01:10:54,861
Yes.

1124
01:10:54,941 --> 01:10:56,461
I found this photo there, sir.

1125
01:10:57,021 --> 01:11:01,741
And sir, there I came to know that
this man is Ranvir's mother's brother.

1126
01:11:01,821 --> 01:11:03,101
Her elder brother at that.

1127
01:11:06,341 --> 01:11:08,421
What the heck! Yet another uncle.

1128
01:11:08,501 --> 01:11:09,581
Uncles galore.

1129
01:11:09,661 --> 01:11:13,821
And I also found out that this man
had gone missing a few years ago.

1130
01:11:13,941 --> 01:11:17,781
No problem. Your promotion is on.
Your salary will be double from next year.

1131
01:11:18,101 --> 01:11:18,621
Find him.

1132
01:11:18,741 --> 01:11:19,101
Yes.

1133
01:11:19,221 --> 01:11:20,261
Find him. Here.

1134
01:11:21,141 --> 01:11:22,141
He also went missing.

1135
01:11:23,301 --> 01:11:25,221
All of them are forgetful.

1136
01:11:30,261 --> 01:11:34,221
Flat no. 801.801.

1137
01:11:34,501 --> 01:11:38,941
Remember this. Either get the sign
tonight or resign from this business.

1138
01:11:39,541 --> 01:11:40,541
Get it?

1139
01:11:44,941 --> 01:11:50,781
Leave me. You don't who I am.
Leave me. I will get you arrested.

1140
01:11:51,221 --> 01:11:51,861
Leave me. Where are you taking me?

1141
01:11:51,941 --> 01:11:53,741
Keep quiet or I'll blow your head off.

1142
01:11:53,861 --> 01:11:55,621
What are you talking about? Let me go.

1143
01:11:55,701 --> 01:11:57,341
Forget the servant. Find the boss first.

1144
01:11:58,061 --> 01:11:59,741
Tell me where is the uncle and nephew.

1145
01:12:00,181 --> 01:12:01,181
Shall we call the police?

1146
01:12:02,221 --> 01:12:05,301
Pizza arrives first in Mumbai.
And then the fire brigade.

1147
01:12:05,781 --> 01:12:06,941
And then the police follow.

1148
01:12:07,581 --> 01:12:10,901
So order pizza first. Do they have guns?

1149
01:12:14,541 --> 01:12:14,821
Leave me.

1150
01:12:14,941 --> 01:12:15,341
Shut up!

1151
01:12:15,621 --> 01:12:16,941
Darn it. Run.

1152
01:12:20,781 --> 01:12:21,221
Come on.

1153
01:12:21,301 --> 01:12:22,581
Where the hell is everyone?

1154
01:12:22,701 --> 01:12:23,701
Come on.

1155
01:12:24,621 --> 01:12:25,861
Run. Run.

1156
01:12:25,941 --> 01:12:28,261
I am the secretary. I cannot run like this.

1157
01:12:32,381 --> 01:12:34,821
I am the secretary. He
is calling me a servant.

1158
01:12:46,101 --> 01:12:49,701
Idiot. Rascal. Knucklehead.

1159
01:12:50,381 --> 01:12:54,621
The people I was thinking
of throwing out of the society,

1160
01:12:54,781 --> 01:12:59,301
today those very people saved
my life risking their own lives.

1161
01:12:59,541 --> 01:13:04,541
You are ungrateful. You are an idiot.
Please forgive me. Please. Please.

1162
01:13:04,741 --> 01:13:05,501
Please.

1163
01:13:05,621 --> 01:13:06,621
It's okay.

1164
01:13:08,861 --> 01:13:11,421
Kukreja, you will always
remain a contractor.

1165
01:13:12,181 --> 01:13:13,381
You'll never become a builder.

1166
01:13:13,741 --> 01:13:15,581
Salim, he is not a man.

1167
01:13:16,101 --> 01:13:18,341
He is a cocktail between.
Rajnikant and Gandhi.

1168
01:13:18,741 --> 01:13:22,941
I have tried so many times.
He survives every time.

1169
01:13:23,101 --> 01:13:24,861
I am coming in two days.

1170
01:13:25,341 --> 01:13:31,301
If you don't get the job done by then, Kukreja
will not see the light of the next day.

1171
01:13:31,381 --> 01:13:34,141
Boss, don't say such things.

1172
01:13:34,261 --> 01:13:38,421
If you can't do it, then call
my brother. And call his men.

1173
01:13:38,621 --> 01:13:42,061
There are only two days left.
Heard that? Only two days.

1174
01:13:42,701 --> 01:13:47,941
Not only a contractor. Kukreja
will become a builder. For sure.

1175
01:13:59,941 --> 01:14:03,581
What are you looking
at? Go and eat that rascal.

1176
01:14:11,901 --> 01:14:12,901
Yes.

1177
01:14:15,261 --> 01:14:16,261
What?

1178
01:14:18,941 --> 01:14:23,461
Well done. Well done, champ. Well done.

1179
01:14:23,861 --> 01:14:28,421
Bring him by the first flight. He
should be here tomorrow morning.

1180
01:14:28,541 --> 01:14:30,621
Well done. Well done.

1181
01:14:31,741 --> 01:14:34,781
Why didn't you let me sit in that bus? Why?

1182
01:14:35,221 --> 01:14:37,581
Calm down. What is the need for
buses when there is such a nice car?

1183
01:14:37,701 --> 01:14:38,701
Really?

1184
01:14:43,741 --> 01:14:44,741
Hello.

1185
01:14:46,141 --> 01:14:48,301
Yes. I am Ranvir. I had come
for the audition of Gulabo.

1186
01:14:48,421 --> 01:14:49,141
Let me hear it too.

1187
01:14:49,221 --> 01:14:51,181
Yes, yes. One minute. Yes.

1188
01:14:53,221 --> 01:14:53,461
Yes.

1189
01:14:53,621 --> 01:14:55,101
What happened? What are they saying?

1190
01:14:55,941 --> 01:14:56,941
Yes. Thank you.

1191
01:14:58,941 --> 01:14:59,941
What happened?

1192
01:15:01,901 --> 01:15:03,461
Hey, tell me. What did they say?

1193
01:15:09,661 --> 01:15:11,181
For the semi finals, your selection...

1194
01:15:12,661 --> 01:15:13,101
Has been done.

1195
01:15:13,181 --> 01:15:14,381
Wow.

1196
01:15:15,101 --> 01:15:15,741
I am going to dance like this.

1197
01:15:15,821 --> 01:15:17,221
You were going to cry, weren't you?

1198
01:15:47,381 --> 01:15:48,501
I think you are joking here.

1199
01:15:49,941 --> 01:15:53,501
Hey, I am telling you. I am
a builder. Not a gangster.

1200
01:15:54,301 --> 01:15:56,181
Just sell it and take
the sum of Rs 50 million.

1201
01:15:56,341 --> 01:15:58,021
That is it. Take this.

1202
01:15:59,621 --> 01:16:02,101
You don't have to do anything.
You just have to sign. Read it.

1203
01:16:02,181 --> 01:16:03,621
The sum of Rs 50 million is a lot.

1204
01:16:14,861 --> 01:16:17,221
Look, Mr Kukreja.

1205
01:16:17,341 --> 01:16:21,541
Stop dreaming of making a
building on our ancestral land.

1206
01:16:22,141 --> 01:16:23,941
You will never be able to get the land.

1207
01:16:27,861 --> 01:16:29,181
Come on. That is okay.

1208
01:16:31,581 --> 01:16:35,301
Here you are. Your youth. Take
this. Even you can take a look.

1209
01:16:37,381 --> 01:16:38,741
I am sure you know them.

1210
01:16:39,661 --> 01:16:41,581
They were running a kite shop in Rohtak.

1211
01:16:42,181 --> 01:16:45,541
I called them by flight.
So that he can meet you.

1212
01:16:46,221 --> 01:16:49,261
They are restless to claim
their right on their ancestral land.

1213
01:16:51,061 --> 01:16:52,061
Uncle, they...

1214
01:16:52,181 --> 01:16:53,221
Don't worry about them.

1215
01:16:55,701 --> 01:16:56,701
Who are they?

1216
01:16:56,941 --> 01:16:57,581
Your uncle. Take a look.

1217
01:16:57,661 --> 01:17:00,581
Whose uncle? Please get out of here.

1218
01:17:19,941 --> 01:17:20,901
Yes.

1219
01:17:20,941 --> 01:17:24,941
Just as kids are born every day in the houses of
people a new uncle is born here every day. I am...

1220
01:17:25,541 --> 01:17:29,581
Suresh is not my real brother,
but he is like my elder brother.

1221
01:17:31,461 --> 01:17:35,181
His father, the great Parvat
Singh used to work at our place.

1222
01:17:35,301 --> 01:17:38,501
Your maternal grandfather
used to treat him as his son.

1223
01:17:38,701 --> 01:17:41,701
Suresh and I have been brought up together.

1224
01:17:43,101 --> 01:17:46,781
After I went off to London and
after the marriage of Shakuntala,

1225
01:17:47,541 --> 01:17:49,501
Suresh disappeared somewhere.

1226
01:17:50,701 --> 01:17:51,701
Along with

1227
01:17:53,221 --> 01:17:54,941
some money and some jewellery.

1228
01:17:56,221 --> 01:17:57,221
A thief.

1229
01:17:58,341 --> 01:18:00,941
And today? Today, he has
been found after so long.

1230
01:18:01,461 --> 01:18:03,661
And the scoundrel has shown
his true colours once more.

1231
01:18:05,501 --> 01:18:06,701
Please forgive me, sir.

1232
01:18:08,141 --> 01:18:10,261
But these people should be
hung downwards from a tree

1233
01:18:10,461 --> 01:18:11,621
and they should be treated very
badly and thrashed with a stick and...

1234
01:18:11,741 --> 01:18:15,141
Bhairav. Bhairav. Don't be rude.

1235
01:18:19,581 --> 01:18:20,581
Listen to me.

1236
01:18:21,901 --> 01:18:22,941
Make a call at the village.

1237
01:18:27,421 --> 01:18:30,181
Come on. Yes. Yes.
Please. Please, make a call.

1238
01:18:30,781 --> 01:18:32,301
Tell them that I am coming there as well.

1239
01:18:32,421 --> 01:18:35,061
After twenty years, I will sit with
you and recite poems for you.

1240
01:18:35,821 --> 01:18:38,141
Decked up and with attitude,
Rajput... And all of that.

1241
01:18:38,221 --> 01:18:39,901
I told you, Dholu.

1242
01:18:41,461 --> 01:18:46,061
Everything will be fine. Don't
worry at all. Don't worry at all.

1243
01:18:46,541 --> 01:18:47,941
Just listen to everything and speak only after that.
- Raichand.

1244
01:18:48,101 --> 01:18:52,901
Hey, dear, we don't have to carry our
land and property when we die. Don't worry.

1245
01:19:02,821 --> 01:19:05,301
I think you have really
become a priest. Yes.

1246
01:19:06,541 --> 01:19:07,661
It is a good idea though.

1247
01:19:08,061 --> 01:19:14,101
Whenever there is a difficult situation you can
get relaxed after saying something spiritual.

1248
01:19:14,581 --> 01:19:15,621
Exit.

1249
01:19:16,181 --> 01:19:17,741
'Dholu, don't worry.'

1250
01:19:18,541 --> 01:19:20,181
Uncle, there is a fire. 'Don't worry.'

1251
01:19:20,701 --> 01:19:21,941
Earthquake. 'Don't worry at all.'

1252
01:19:22,821 --> 01:19:24,581
This worry will get us in a mess one day.

1253
01:19:26,221 --> 01:19:28,141
Hey, watch my dance.
It is for the semi finals.

1254
01:19:28,821 --> 01:19:29,821
What happened here?

1255
01:19:30,501 --> 01:19:32,661
Gul, leave me alone for some time.

1256
01:19:34,421 --> 01:19:34,741
Why?

1257
01:19:34,941 --> 01:19:36,061
Because I am in a bad mood.

1258
01:19:39,221 --> 01:19:42,941
I had a nice property. And I
lost it because of a new problem.

1259
01:19:48,461 --> 01:19:49,461
Okay, tell me something.

1260
01:19:51,061 --> 01:19:52,341
What would you do with the land?

1261
01:19:57,941 --> 01:19:59,221
I would have bought a new house.

1262
01:19:59,301 --> 01:19:59,661
Yes.

1263
01:19:59,941 --> 01:20:01,821
Sea facing. Okay? BMW car.

1264
01:20:03,101 --> 01:20:04,181
Okay. Then?

1265
01:20:06,101 --> 01:20:07,901
I would have gone on
a trip around the world.

1266
01:20:08,941 --> 01:20:09,941
Then?

1267
01:20:11,941 --> 01:20:12,941
Then? Then what?

1268
01:20:13,741 --> 01:20:14,741
I would have been rich.

1269
01:20:16,461 --> 01:20:18,301
Hey, so what is the problem?

1270
01:20:19,381 --> 01:20:23,701
If it is about money, when I win the dance
competition I will give the entire money to you.

1271
01:20:24,261 --> 01:20:26,501
You will be able to buy all
your stuff with that, right?

1272
01:20:30,421 --> 01:20:31,421
I am here, right?

1273
01:20:39,941 --> 01:20:42,781
Are you that confident? Will you win?

1274
01:20:44,101 --> 01:20:45,101
Yes.

1275
01:20:45,501 --> 01:20:47,421
You are the one who
says that I dance very well.

1276
01:20:47,901 --> 01:20:50,541
If I spread my wings, I
will win Mumbai over.

1277
01:20:54,301 --> 01:20:55,421
Do you trust me that much?

1278
01:20:56,581 --> 01:20:58,621
Yes. Why not?

1279
01:20:59,661 --> 01:21:04,181
You are a Rajput. And that is the word of a
Rajput. I am sure you will keep your word.

1280
01:21:09,541 --> 01:21:10,541
Come on.

1281
01:21:11,941 --> 01:21:12,541
Dance for me.

1282
01:21:12,941 --> 01:21:13,941
Okay.

1283
01:21:15,621 --> 01:21:17,341
Where have you been for all these years?

1284
01:21:17,701 --> 01:21:18,701
Where?

1285
01:21:19,061 --> 01:21:22,381
Without you, my whole life was lonely.

1286
01:21:22,861 --> 01:21:25,461
Suresh is my elder brother.

1287
01:21:25,581 --> 01:21:26,821
Did you hear that, sir?

1288
01:21:27,341 --> 01:21:31,821
Suresh. Suresh. He means elder brother.

1289
01:21:32,341 --> 01:21:36,861
Elder brother. He is Suresh.
The real heir of this land.

1290
01:21:37,221 --> 01:21:40,821
And you can see the love between brothers.

1291
01:21:41,341 --> 01:21:46,741
According to Hindu undivided property law
elder brother is the first person to inherit.

1292
01:21:47,421 --> 01:21:52,261
So sir, actually this is his
signed will. For my name.

1293
01:21:52,501 --> 01:21:54,501
Will? What will?

1294
01:21:54,661 --> 01:21:59,821
Mr Singh, after seeing all this I am
convinced that Kukreja's claim is correct.

1295
01:21:59,901 --> 01:22:00,901
What is this, Mr Pudhe?

1296
01:22:01,301 --> 01:22:04,941
In order to record the statement of our uncle
you got him here all the way from the village.

1297
01:22:05,341 --> 01:22:08,701
Since two weeks, you have been
verifying all his documents. It is okay.

1298
01:22:09,261 --> 01:22:11,661
But you agreed to the
statement of this man in one go?

1299
01:22:11,941 --> 01:22:17,221
My name is Swatantra Bharat Bhushan.
I have made an IAS officer go to jail.

1300
01:22:17,381 --> 01:22:18,581
He was charged for corruption.

1301
01:22:18,941 --> 01:22:21,301
In my presence, think over the
decision carefully before you take it.

1302
01:22:21,381 --> 01:22:22,381
Who is this?

1303
01:22:23,541 --> 01:22:25,821
You are absolutely right, Mr Bhushan.

1304
01:22:26,381 --> 01:22:29,381
But I really have no
choice. I have no other way.

1305
01:22:29,661 --> 01:22:33,261
Dholu. He is your elder uncle. Greet him.

1306
01:22:33,741 --> 01:22:35,941
Suresh, he is Dholu. Your nephew.

1307
01:22:36,781 --> 01:22:39,781
He is the son of our
younger sister Shakuntala.

1308
01:22:40,701 --> 01:22:42,021
Shakuntala is no more.

1309
01:22:43,221 --> 01:22:44,221
She is gone.

1310
01:22:44,901 --> 01:22:47,821
And he is Shakuntala's
sign. Take his blessings.

1311
01:22:48,421 --> 01:22:50,341
The same sign that you
are giving off to Kukreja.

1312
01:22:50,461 --> 01:22:51,541
Dholu, take his blessings.

1313
01:22:51,701 --> 01:22:52,701
Greetings.

1314
01:22:54,621 --> 01:22:58,541
Suresh, let us go home.
We have lots to talk about.

1315
01:22:58,621 --> 01:23:02,941
Yes. Talk. Talk as much as you want. Go wherever
you want to after you give your thumb print here.

1316
01:23:03,461 --> 01:23:05,941
I will send you tickets for
the flight. Come on. Come on.

1317
01:23:06,301 --> 01:23:07,301
Come on.

1318
01:23:08,101 --> 01:23:10,701
Come on. Come on. Let's do it.

1319
01:23:10,821 --> 01:23:11,941
Suresh, sign here.

1320
01:23:14,061 --> 01:23:15,941
Come on. You have to sign at three places.

1321
01:23:16,061 --> 01:23:19,781
At this point, at this point and
the last one would be at this point.

1322
01:23:19,941 --> 01:23:20,541
Here you are.

1323
01:23:20,661 --> 01:23:21,661
Come on. Let's do it.

1324
01:23:22,101 --> 01:23:25,541
Come on, sign it!

1325
01:23:26,581 --> 01:23:29,221
Yes. Yes. Do sign.

1326
01:23:31,941 --> 01:23:32,581
Suresh?

1327
01:23:32,661 --> 01:23:33,661
Hey!

1328
01:23:40,141 --> 01:23:41,341
Want to give your thumb print?

1329
01:23:43,141 --> 01:23:44,141
Rude man.

1330
01:23:47,861 --> 01:23:48,861
Suresh Singh.

1331
01:23:49,901 --> 01:23:52,061
You are under the oath of the late Thakur.

1332
01:23:53,221 --> 01:23:54,421
If you are lying...

1333
01:23:54,781 --> 01:23:57,821
Let him go ahead and lie. Let him lie.

1334
01:23:58,941 --> 01:23:59,101
Hey!

1335
01:23:59,221 --> 01:24:02,781
We will make him meet Mr Thakur.

1336
01:24:03,741 --> 01:24:05,701
If you have any shame do go ahead and put your
thumb impression. Even I am standing here.

1337
01:24:05,821 --> 01:24:07,741
No, no, don't do that.

1338
01:24:08,541 --> 01:24:13,181
Hey, hey, don't be scared. Don't be scared. Put
the impression. Come on. Put the impression.

1339
01:24:13,701 --> 01:24:14,781
Can you see that, Mr Pudhe?

1340
01:24:15,181 --> 01:24:18,541
Hey, come on, put the thumb
impression. Come on. Hey, what is this.

1341
01:24:18,621 --> 01:24:21,061
This land doesn't belong to me.

1342
01:24:22,341 --> 01:24:23,341
This land

1343
01:24:24,701 --> 01:24:29,421
was given by his father to
his daughter called Shakuntala.

1344
01:24:29,901 --> 01:24:30,661
That's it!

1345
01:24:30,781 --> 01:24:32,301
Hey, you told me that it is your land.

1346
01:24:32,581 --> 01:24:34,581
Suresh. Suresh... Someone stop him.

1347
01:24:34,701 --> 01:24:35,701
He...

1348
01:24:39,741 --> 01:24:44,061
According to the situation and
the papers, I have no other choice.

1349
01:24:44,181 --> 01:24:45,621
What do you mean?

1350
01:24:46,141 --> 01:24:49,501
According to the NOC, they are
the real owners of the property.

1351
01:24:49,701 --> 01:24:53,261
Yes. Actually my nephew
is the real owner of the land.

1352
01:24:53,541 --> 01:24:56,741
The land belonged to his mother.
And now he is the rightful owner of it.

1353
01:24:56,861 --> 01:24:58,941
Right, Dholu. Great.

1354
01:25:03,701 --> 01:25:06,061
'Dance India. All India.'

1355
01:25:15,941 --> 01:25:19,821
Gul seems a little
heavier on going to the city.

1356
01:25:20,181 --> 01:25:21,861
It seems the water of
the city has suited her.

1357
01:25:21,941 --> 01:25:25,661
Hey, blind man. Not Gul
but your brain has become fat.

1358
01:25:26,461 --> 01:25:27,581
Hey, she is the same girl.

1359
01:25:56,941 --> 01:25:58,781
You have won the semi final.

1360
01:26:01,141 --> 01:26:03,061
But the grand finale is still left.

1361
01:26:04,261 --> 01:26:05,421
Grand finale.

1362
01:26:11,661 --> 01:26:12,661
What are you thinking of?

1363
01:26:16,421 --> 01:26:17,421
Till yesterday.

1364
01:26:18,181 --> 01:26:19,781
Till yesterday, my village was my world.

1365
01:26:21,541 --> 01:26:22,541
And today,

1366
01:26:24,341 --> 01:26:25,941
I am seeing a completely different world.

1367
01:26:28,941 --> 01:26:31,781
You have made an unseen
dream turn into reality.

1368
01:26:33,581 --> 01:26:34,581
It is just the beginning.

1369
01:26:35,821 --> 01:26:37,621
Now you will be very famous in India.

1370
01:26:38,661 --> 01:26:39,941
Producers will run after you.

1371
01:26:41,101 --> 01:26:42,141
And they will give you offers for films.

1372
01:26:42,261 --> 01:26:42,861
Really?

1373
01:26:43,101 --> 01:26:43,461
Yes.

1374
01:26:44,141 --> 01:26:45,941
By the way, I have a lot
of fun during the shoot.

1375
01:26:46,061 --> 01:26:48,101
I had seen a serial shooting in Mendava.

1376
01:26:48,221 --> 01:26:48,581
Really.

1377
01:26:48,781 --> 01:26:51,461
In that, the girl was telling
the hero about her heart.

1378
01:26:53,461 --> 01:26:54,221
Should I do it?

1379
01:26:54,341 --> 01:26:57,301
Yes. You will rehearse as well.

1380
01:26:57,621 --> 01:26:58,621
Okay.

1381
01:27:08,941 --> 01:27:10,061
My lips haven't yet

1382
01:27:11,781 --> 01:27:12,941
told you anything.

1383
01:27:13,781 --> 01:27:16,261
But don't my eyes say anything to you?

1384
01:27:17,941 --> 01:27:21,061
When I run my fingers through my hair.

1385
01:27:24,181 --> 01:27:26,501
If you would have noticed
carefully, you would have known

1386
01:27:28,341 --> 01:27:29,661
that I keep on writing your name.

1387
01:27:32,341 --> 01:27:33,341
Did you...

1388
01:27:33,861 --> 01:27:35,821
Didn't you ever feel this love?

1389
01:27:38,181 --> 01:27:39,181
Tell me.

1390
01:27:42,741 --> 01:27:44,381
Yes, I think.

1391
01:27:46,341 --> 01:27:47,701
I love you very much.

1392
01:27:53,341 --> 01:27:55,621
Did you see that? Even I can act so much.

1393
01:27:56,461 --> 01:27:58,301
We must talk to the
director about me as well.

1394
01:27:59,541 --> 01:28:00,941
Now you wouldn't give me attention.

1395
01:28:01,701 --> 01:28:04,141
Yes. By the way, this is right.

1396
01:28:12,941 --> 01:28:15,701
By the way, whatever
I told you wasn't an act.

1397
01:28:17,661 --> 01:28:19,221
And even what I told you wasn't an act.

1398
01:28:20,341 --> 01:28:21,341
Boy.

1399
01:28:27,741 --> 01:28:30,261
We will have the engagement here in Mumbai.

1400
01:28:31,181 --> 01:28:31,461
That's good.

1401
01:28:32,181 --> 01:28:36,181
And the wedding will take place in
Rajasthan. After the final program of Gul.

1402
01:28:36,661 --> 01:28:40,341
And I will come from the bride's side.

1403
01:28:40,661 --> 01:28:41,141
Father.

1404
01:28:41,221 --> 01:28:43,501
Thank you, God.

1405
01:28:47,701 --> 01:28:50,621
That is it. We just
need to find a good date.

1406
01:28:50,861 --> 01:28:51,541
Bhairav.

1407
01:28:51,621 --> 01:28:51,861
Yes, sir.

1408
01:28:51,941 --> 01:28:52,861
Let us know of a good date.

1409
01:28:52,941 --> 01:28:55,821
Day after tomorrow. It is a
full moon night. It is nice date.

1410
01:28:55,901 --> 01:28:56,381
Okay.

1411
01:28:56,861 --> 01:28:57,821
Engagement on the full moon night.

1412
01:28:57,901 --> 01:28:58,901
Bhairav.

1413
01:28:59,421 --> 01:29:03,861
Come on, come on. Come
here. Yes. Be happy. Yes.

1414
01:29:09,381 --> 01:29:09,821
One minute.

1415
01:29:10,261 --> 01:29:11,261
What did I tell you?

1416
01:29:11,541 --> 01:29:12,221
Yes, Mr Lal. Tell me.

1417
01:29:12,461 --> 01:29:16,541
How are you, my friend? My brother?
Get ready to listen to good news.

1418
01:29:16,941 --> 01:29:20,301
I have got an offer of Rs
150 million for your plot.

1419
01:29:20,381 --> 01:29:21,421
Yes, Rs 150 million.

1420
01:29:21,541 --> 01:29:24,541
But this time I want 10% commission.

1421
01:29:24,861 --> 01:29:28,861
And the party is coming to Mumbai in a few days to
finalise the deal. You tell me. Should I tell them to...

1422
01:29:28,941 --> 01:29:29,301
Mr Lal,

1423
01:29:29,421 --> 01:29:30,421
Yes?

1424
01:29:30,741 --> 01:29:31,861
I will call you later. Okay?

1425
01:29:32,421 --> 01:29:33,421
Hey, but...

1426
01:29:36,541 --> 01:29:37,941
What are you doing? I will get hurt.

1427
01:29:39,181 --> 01:29:43,741
Hey, call those goons now. The ones
who were recommended by Stanley.

1428
01:29:44,461 --> 01:29:45,821
I have called them.
They are sitting outside.

1429
01:29:45,941 --> 01:29:46,941
Yes.

1430
01:29:48,461 --> 01:29:51,301
Fool, even you will turn
me into a gangster like you.

1431
01:29:53,061 --> 01:29:55,821
And if this is what you
want, this is what you will get.

1432
01:29:57,821 --> 01:30:01,381
Hey, but we lost out on the land, right? So
what is the point of calling those goons?

1433
01:30:02,941 --> 01:30:05,941
Have you forgotten Meerut?
What did they do in Meerut?

1434
01:30:06,621 --> 01:30:09,101
If you lose from the law, take control.

1435
01:30:10,501 --> 01:30:11,781
Take control of the land.

1436
01:30:15,261 --> 01:30:17,301
I hope no one among you is a Rajasthani.

1437
01:30:24,061 --> 01:30:26,301
Okay. Start their work from tomorrow.

1438
01:30:26,821 --> 01:30:28,261
Give them advance. Give them money.

1439
01:30:28,741 --> 01:30:29,741
Okay.

1440
01:30:30,661 --> 01:30:34,581
Hey, this fool. He has called me again. He has
called me again. He doesn't spare me. Get lost.

1441
01:30:35,581 --> 01:30:36,581
Darn it!

1442
01:30:38,021 --> 01:30:41,181
'Hello. Kuki. Kuki?'

1443
01:30:41,301 --> 01:30:43,621
God of mobile.

1444
01:30:43,861 --> 01:30:46,261
'Hello, Kuki?'

1445
01:30:46,421 --> 01:30:48,621
'Hey, fool. I am waiting
for you at the airport.'

1446
01:30:49,021 --> 01:30:53,221
'You had told me that you will wait
for me with a garland. Where are you?'

1447
01:30:53,341 --> 01:30:54,701
Hey, you are a fool. Your father...

1448
01:30:54,781 --> 01:30:56,341
'Kuki.'

1449
01:30:56,941 --> 01:31:00,941
Hey, did you understand what I said?
Everyone must surround the land and sit.

1450
01:31:01,661 --> 01:31:04,181
No one must move from their place. No one.

1451
01:31:04,661 --> 01:31:08,261
Let there be storm, winds or rain. Let
there be the ultimate natural calamity.

1452
01:31:08,901 --> 01:31:11,141
We must take the land in control. Got it?

1453
01:31:11,941 --> 01:31:12,341
Yes.

1454
01:31:12,661 --> 01:31:14,341
Kuki, what if we have to use the bathroom?

1455
01:31:14,701 --> 01:31:15,701
What?

1456
01:31:16,501 --> 01:31:17,501
Bathroom?

1457
01:31:18,501 --> 01:31:21,381
Hey, one minute. A very important
task has come up. One minute, okay?

1458
01:31:21,701 --> 01:31:25,421
Yes. Do it. Do it. Do it. Open it.

1459
01:31:26,021 --> 01:31:28,941
Open it. I will make you
do it. Open it. Open it.

1460
01:31:30,501 --> 01:31:32,741
Hey, what are you doing?
The boy has to urinate.

1461
01:31:37,661 --> 01:31:41,741
What happened? Listen
to me. I know you are a fool.

1462
01:31:41,941 --> 01:31:43,061
You don't make mistakes.

1463
01:31:43,181 --> 01:31:46,821
But if you make any mistake today,
I will bury you alive, fool. Get lost.

1464
01:31:47,261 --> 01:31:48,741
I hope no one else has any questions.

1465
01:31:48,861 --> 01:31:52,661
Sir, come here once. Look at
what is happening downstairs.

1466
01:32:01,741 --> 01:32:04,821
Hey, I had told you. You
should have brought a tent. Tent.

1467
01:32:04,901 --> 01:32:07,181
It is monsoon. Hey, don't
you understand what I tell you?

1468
01:32:07,461 --> 01:32:09,341
Even if half a mantra is mispronounced...

1469
01:32:09,661 --> 01:32:11,741
I hope you know how
grave the results for that are.

1470
01:32:11,821 --> 01:32:12,581
Yes, sir.

1471
01:32:12,661 --> 01:32:13,101
Do remember.

1472
01:32:13,221 --> 01:32:13,581
Yes.

1473
01:32:13,661 --> 01:32:14,701
Okay, keep this here and fill it up.

1474
01:32:14,781 --> 01:32:16,941
Like water and flowers and other things.

1475
01:32:17,061 --> 01:32:17,781
Greetings to you, Bhairav.

1476
01:32:17,861 --> 01:32:18,741
Yes. Greetings to you too.

1477
01:32:18,861 --> 01:32:20,341
Greetings to you, Bhairav.

1478
01:32:20,461 --> 01:32:23,141
I am finally at peace
because of your blessings.

1479
01:32:23,261 --> 01:32:23,861
Wait for me.

1480
01:32:23,941 --> 01:32:26,021
Hey, don't close my
eyes. Don't close my eyes.

1481
01:32:26,141 --> 01:32:27,541
No, no, no, they will be opened right away.

1482
01:32:27,621 --> 01:32:28,701
Hey, not like that.

1483
01:32:28,821 --> 01:32:29,381
Yes, yes, move it. Move it.
Move it away from his eyes.

1484
01:32:29,461 --> 01:32:31,341
Don't worry about that.

1485
01:32:36,661 --> 01:32:39,581
Dear, the auspicious time for the
engagement is here. Come here.

1486
01:32:44,341 --> 01:32:45,941
My daughter is looking very nice.

1487
01:32:46,301 --> 01:32:48,261
Come on, the auspicious time is passing by.

1488
01:32:49,101 --> 01:32:52,621
Hey, have you gone mad?
Yes? Put the gun down.

1489
01:32:53,221 --> 01:32:56,101
The engagement isn't done yet. We will do
this after the engagement. Gun shots and all.

1490
01:32:56,221 --> 01:33:01,301
Such a big function. And you
didn't call your neighbour. Very bad.

1491
01:33:01,381 --> 01:33:02,141
What is this?

1492
01:33:02,381 --> 01:33:02,741
Ranvir.

1493
01:33:02,861 --> 01:33:05,901
Ranvir. Leave the girl. I am warning you.
- I am Kukreja.

1494
01:33:06,021 --> 01:33:06,461
Leave me.

1495
01:33:06,621 --> 01:33:07,381
Girl, please wait.

1496
01:33:07,461 --> 01:33:07,821
Dholu.

1497
01:33:07,941 --> 01:33:08,941
Calm down.

1498
01:33:09,181 --> 01:33:10,941
It is such an auspicious occasion.

1499
01:33:12,581 --> 01:33:15,421
I'll get the land, you will sign
the documents. Both will be done.

1500
01:33:16,061 --> 01:33:18,421
Hey, she is looking so nice.

1501
01:33:18,781 --> 01:33:19,941
What do they call in Rajasthani?

1502
01:33:20,061 --> 01:33:21,061
Sir, beautiful girl.

1503
01:33:21,141 --> 01:33:21,621
Yes.

1504
01:33:21,741 --> 01:33:22,581
Hey, hey, hey.

1505
01:33:22,701 --> 01:33:23,101
Kukreja.

1506
01:33:23,221 --> 01:33:23,581
Stop.

1507
01:33:23,861 --> 01:33:24,221
Father.

1508
01:33:24,341 --> 01:33:25,381
Leave my kid alone.

1509
01:33:26,381 --> 01:33:30,061
You want the land, right? Give me the papers.
I will give you the land. Give me the papers.

1510
01:33:30,181 --> 01:33:31,061
I will sign it.

1511
01:33:31,261 --> 01:33:34,621
Hey, no, uncle. I don't need your sign.

1512
01:33:34,701 --> 01:33:36,661
You have already signed the NOC, right?

1513
01:33:37,261 --> 01:33:39,061
Now the star is your nephew.

1514
01:33:40,501 --> 01:33:41,501
Ranvir.

1515
01:33:42,101 --> 01:33:44,141
Hey, the one who has
the guts to run and win.

1516
01:33:44,221 --> 01:33:44,661
What?

1517
01:33:44,781 --> 01:33:46,461
And also win over the Sun has...

1518
01:33:47,181 --> 01:33:50,941
Hey, sign now. Sign. Sir, please
sign. Please. I am a huge fan of yours.

1519
01:33:51,901 --> 01:33:52,741
Ranvir, don't sign.

1520
01:33:52,861 --> 01:33:54,101
Hey, quiet. Keep quiet.

1521
01:33:54,181 --> 01:33:59,861
Hey, make it quick. I don't have time. Hey,
take it. Hold it. Hold it. Hey, fool. Quiet.

1522
01:34:01,061 --> 01:34:02,781
Hey! Just leave her.

1523
01:34:02,861 --> 01:34:04,541
Hey, look. Look.

1524
01:34:04,901 --> 01:34:07,901
Hey, you idiot. Leave
me. Ranvir, no. Ranvir, no.

1525
01:34:07,941 --> 01:34:09,181
Leave the girl's neck.

1526
01:34:14,501 --> 01:34:16,141
Hey, take it. Take it.

1527
01:34:17,541 --> 01:34:20,141
Now give it to me. Here you
are. I have given her back.

1528
01:34:22,461 --> 01:34:27,461
Uncle says that for a Rajput,
duty is the biggest thing.

1529
01:34:28,221 --> 01:34:29,221
Not this land.

1530
01:34:29,341 --> 01:34:32,061
Hey, dear. Your uncle and you...

1531
01:34:32,461 --> 01:34:35,221
Stop teaching each other
about the history of Rajputs.

1532
01:34:35,381 --> 01:34:37,661
You signed it and I gave the
girl back. The matter is over.

1533
01:34:37,781 --> 01:34:38,941
Congrats for the engagement.

1534
01:34:45,341 --> 01:34:46,341
Salim.

1535
01:34:46,941 --> 01:34:49,621
Greetings. Greetings.

1536
01:34:49,701 --> 01:34:51,901
Salim.

1537
01:34:53,941 --> 01:34:54,941
Salim.

1538
01:35:00,141 --> 01:35:04,861
Salim, you have reached at the right time.
At the perfect time. Just like police.

1539
01:35:04,941 --> 01:35:06,061
After all the work is done.

1540
01:35:06,781 --> 01:35:07,381
Salim.

1541
01:35:07,461 --> 01:35:11,181
Salim, look at this. We have the land in
our control. And the world is at our feet.

1542
01:35:11,261 --> 01:35:14,381
You fool. You don't take my calls.

1543
01:35:15,181 --> 01:35:20,221
That long car has been
bought by you with my money.

1544
01:35:20,941 --> 01:35:22,181
Even the mobile was
bought by my money, right?

1545
01:35:22,261 --> 01:35:23,741
Yes, all of it was yours, Salim.

1546
01:35:24,101 --> 01:35:28,021
I asked you to buy a small
piece of land. You couldn't buy it.

1547
01:35:28,661 --> 01:35:31,581
The work that couldn't be done by
you was done by me at a snap of a finger.

1548
01:35:31,661 --> 01:35:32,661
Meaning?

1549
01:35:36,301 --> 01:35:37,301
Look.

1550
01:35:38,741 --> 01:35:43,101
Look at him. I have given
him an offer of Rs 150 million.

1551
01:35:43,221 --> 01:35:43,661
What?

1552
01:35:43,741 --> 01:35:45,541
He took the project in his hands.

1553
01:35:47,381 --> 01:35:48,821
So give this to me. And you.

1554
01:35:48,941 --> 01:35:49,221
Yes?

1555
01:35:49,621 --> 01:35:49,941
Go.

1556
01:35:50,141 --> 01:35:50,421
Where?

1557
01:35:50,501 --> 01:35:50,781
Go home.

1558
01:35:50,901 --> 01:35:51,141
Where?

1559
01:35:51,541 --> 01:35:52,781
Salim.

1560
01:35:53,301 --> 01:35:55,661
Salim, I have taken care of
this project like my own child.

1561
01:35:56,141 --> 01:35:59,141
Salim, that wasn't right on your part. No.

1562
01:36:00,021 --> 01:36:01,021
Hey, stop.

1563
01:36:02,421 --> 01:36:03,421
Where are you going?

1564
01:36:04,541 --> 01:36:05,621
They are my men.

1565
01:36:06,781 --> 01:36:07,381
Do something.

1566
01:36:07,741 --> 01:36:08,021
Yes.

1567
01:36:08,141 --> 01:36:09,181
You can go back to Meerut.

1568
01:36:09,581 --> 01:36:12,061
Go by train and buy half a ticket.

1569
01:36:12,501 --> 01:36:15,541
When the TT asks why did you buy
half a ticket? Tell him that you are a kid.

1570
01:36:15,741 --> 01:36:18,941
Go, go away. Go away. Take
his clothes off. Make him nude.

1571
01:36:19,301 --> 01:36:20,941
Get on with it. Everything is mine.

1572
01:36:21,101 --> 01:36:23,821
The whole building standing
here is mine. Don't do this to me.

1573
01:36:24,221 --> 01:36:27,661
I will be ruined. I will
give you all your money.

1574
01:36:29,141 --> 01:36:30,141
Come on.

1575
01:36:30,341 --> 01:36:31,341
Salim.

1576
01:36:32,061 --> 01:36:33,061
Salim.

1577
01:36:34,141 --> 01:36:35,501
Have pity on me.

1578
01:36:36,661 --> 01:36:37,661
Salim.

1579
01:36:45,581 --> 01:36:48,301
Salim, I had to tell you something else.

1580
01:36:59,661 --> 01:37:03,781
He is finally silent. You had a lot of
demands, right? A lot of demands.

1581
01:37:05,261 --> 01:37:06,261
What is this?

1582
01:37:06,941 --> 01:37:10,661
Kukreja Sun City. And not Salim city.

1583
01:37:12,941 --> 01:37:16,301
Clothes? Who took my clothes off?

1584
01:37:20,941 --> 01:37:23,581
What is it? Even you want to have fun?

1585
01:37:24,341 --> 01:37:27,381
Spend your honeymoon
well. She is a good looking girl.

1586
01:37:27,661 --> 01:37:29,541
And if you don't get a place, then...

1587
01:37:29,661 --> 01:37:33,101
What is this? Where have you got it from?

1588
01:37:35,061 --> 01:37:36,141
I'm good at aiming things.

1589
01:37:36,261 --> 01:37:36,861
Move aside!

1590
01:37:36,941 --> 01:37:37,701
No, Dholu. No.

1591
01:37:37,781 --> 01:37:38,861
Dholu, calm down.

1592
01:37:42,661 --> 01:37:44,541
Make it fast. Make it quick.

1593
01:37:55,701 --> 01:37:57,421
Give a check of Rs 200,000 to the fool.

1594
01:37:57,541 --> 01:37:57,901
More?

1595
01:37:58,061 --> 01:38:01,701
Quickly. He got a lot of
abuses from me. A lot of them.

1596
01:38:02,021 --> 01:38:03,381
And he has done a good job, right?

1597
01:38:03,941 --> 01:38:05,821
Okay, sir. I will send it.

1598
01:38:11,181 --> 01:38:14,341
Salim? Is he still alive?

1599
01:38:16,821 --> 01:38:17,301
Hello.

1600
01:38:17,861 --> 01:38:18,901
Mr Kukreja.

1601
01:38:19,061 --> 01:38:20,061
Who is it?

1602
01:38:21,701 --> 01:38:22,701
Ranvir.

1603
01:38:23,301 --> 01:38:27,941
Ranvir? Tell me.

1604
01:38:28,221 --> 01:38:30,101
You are feeling sad. What happened?

1605
01:38:30,261 --> 01:38:31,301
You took everything away.

1606
01:38:31,701 --> 01:38:34,621
Now look, everyone is destined to
have the food they are supposed to eat.

1607
01:38:35,901 --> 01:38:36,141
Right?

1608
01:38:36,221 --> 01:38:37,221
They are.

1609
01:38:38,101 --> 01:38:39,101
Come on. Read it.

1610
01:38:39,581 --> 01:38:40,581
What?

1611
01:38:40,941 --> 01:38:41,941
What are you saying?

1612
01:38:43,581 --> 01:38:44,581
Yes?

1613
01:38:44,861 --> 01:38:45,861
What are you saying?

1614
01:38:48,421 --> 01:38:49,421
Come on, read it.

1615
01:38:49,781 --> 01:38:50,781
Sir, take a look at it.

1616
01:38:51,341 --> 01:38:52,661
He cut the call.

1617
01:38:52,941 --> 01:38:53,461
What?

1618
01:38:53,541 --> 01:38:54,221
Sir, look at this.

1619
01:38:54,381 --> 01:38:55,381
What?

1620
01:38:56,101 --> 01:38:57,101
'Don't worry!'

1621
01:38:59,181 --> 01:39:01,141
Don't worry!

1622
01:39:01,941 --> 01:39:04,621
Don't worry!

1623
01:39:06,181 --> 01:39:09,581
Hey, I thought he is a good man. Now
we cannot see faces on the phone, Ranvir.

1624
01:39:09,861 --> 01:39:11,221
Hey, don't be mad, Ranvir.

1625
01:39:11,661 --> 01:39:14,821
They have made a... Ranvir.
Please. It is a big company.

1626
01:39:15,101 --> 01:39:17,421
They have made an offer of Rs 400 million.

1627
01:39:17,741 --> 01:39:21,661
Rs 400 million. I have
explained them the offer.

1628
01:39:21,821 --> 01:39:23,221
I had told him. He will understand.

1629
01:39:23,621 --> 01:39:25,861
Uncle. Make him explain. Please.

1630
01:39:26,021 --> 01:39:27,941
Yes, dear. Choice is yours.

1631
01:39:28,141 --> 01:39:31,141
Great. Choice is yours. Say yes.

1632
01:39:31,261 --> 01:39:31,541
Mr Lal.

1633
01:39:31,621 --> 01:39:32,621
Yes?

1634
01:39:33,181 --> 01:39:34,941
There is a saying in Raghukul.

1635
01:39:36,341 --> 01:39:38,461
One can lose life but not the given word.

1636
01:39:39,621 --> 01:39:41,941
Ranvir, don't recite poems for me.

1637
01:39:42,781 --> 01:39:45,581
Give me your decision.
You will be super rich.

1638
01:39:46,741 --> 01:39:48,501
Mr Lal, my word is
better than super, right?

1639
01:39:48,821 --> 01:39:50,701
Yes. That is right.

1640
01:39:50,941 --> 01:39:53,661
Bhairav, I forgot to tell you something.

1641
01:39:54,421 --> 01:39:58,461
Cow dung has turned into a gold. The
rates of fertilizer shares are sky high.

1642
01:39:58,621 --> 01:39:59,701
Better than super.

1643
01:39:59,821 --> 01:40:03,461
Hey, what are you saying?
